<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no" ?>
<FinalDraft DocumentType="Script" Template="No" Version="6">

  <DocumentRef DateTime="20260301T194540" id="ddc0b014-049a-46a0-a80b-233f6537fcc0"/>

  <Content>
    <Paragraph Type="Transition" id="5e4db968-bf11-439e-8d7d-b05c77382ffc">
      <Text>COLD OPEN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="27e890ba-a937-4edf-9f5e-bbc96e3bb07f">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 2/8" Page="1" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="VOICE">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>BLACK SCREEN.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="bbbfaed7-b324-4076-8c49-243e58496741">
      <Text>Nothing but darkness. Then— A VOICE. Male. Confident. The kind of voice that's used to being obeyed. But right now, there's an edge to it. Excitement barely contained.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="567205e6-bece-4a24-8ca9-c1864cf661c5">
      <Text>VOICE (V.O.)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="8a3dca63-bd70-425a-8784-7ae6249f26b2">
      <Text>I know it's a shitty shell. That's why I set it up.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="19eb0ac4-6ee8-4c70-84b8-430ea4560083">
      <Text>A beat. Listening to someone on the other end.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="e31aa7ac-e0be-41ae-8500-9c7502db7068">
      <Text>VOICE (V.O.)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="030d5eff-8e0d-4ebf-9a65-d1191bd43214">
      <Text>So don't fucking lecture me about exposure. I'm the one that faked the data.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="7da31db1-f0ae-46d4-89f1-cfe264e40e04">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="f42b4432-277f-4f4f-9820-0cc05942b328">
      <Text>No. Fuck no. My name isn't going anywhere near the books on this.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="3401a5ae-7184-4e67-bc71-5ad6139236dd">
      <Text>The voice is pacing now—we can hear footsteps on hardwood, ice clinking in a glass.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="38ccfc99-22e1-4f14-8fb5-6aeba4dfc3dc">
      <Text>VOICE (V.O.)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="77dfe310-6093-416e-8313-c661f7d3cf33">
      <Text>But we can't close without someone eating the dick with the S.E.C. on the whole transaction. We know that.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="a0fc08af-de28-4dfe-8450-7ed04dc1117b">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="ecd536f5-7a0c-492e-bff6-43bafa24c0bc">
      <Text>No. What?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="c7c1c642-1c5c-4a49-9ce0-a855e91ecd87">
      <Text>(Beat)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="55680f3d-e7d4-4324-ad20-fc1cec2e980d">
      <Text>Fuck you.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d44521d4-e2e5-4d55-869e-aa3113b6eaf6">
      <Text>Then— the voice changes. Shifts. Surprise. Delight.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="cfe84eee-361a-4b78-9456-6e32159e11a4">
      <Text>VOICE (V.O.)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="cc0af42f-1c10-4e6e-84a9-30d8ed0bb78f">
      <Text>Wait— what? He fucking signed it?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="44a4ff9d-cbee-4f56-a13e-e504a16045c6">
      <Text>(Beat.)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="eee8159d-2b92-473d-880a-acee292b638f">
      <Text>Bullshit.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="e285d263-43cd-4128-9d2e-5434dc858b45">
      <Text>(Beat.)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="586752c9-c064-471f-aae0-f5e6d87d192a">
      <Text>You're fucking with me.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="36c57788-fcba-43cc-ba31-2e7703113e80">
      <Text>The longest pause yet. And then—a laugh. Low. Genuine. The laugh of a man who just won a game the other player didn't know he was playing.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="ad84d33a-0be8-4ef6-a910-ef17ab5ff58a">
      <Text>VOICE (V.O.)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="65fd4960-399a-44e3-b085-460a33215e32">
      <Text>Really.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="dce18e12-1ba8-4969-932c-99a58087fcfe">
      <Text>The laugh builds. Ice clinks again.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="082e5b27-baae-47d8-a409-d47ffd3fe877">
      <Text>VOICE (V.O.)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="4e37ef03-89b4-4edc-b3bc-35adf2b48c07">
      <Text>(savoring it)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="80095915-4ef0-48c5-bb0e-c84eca7f870a">
      <Text>That dumb, beautiful Boy Scout son of a bitch actually signed it.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="1a587a6e-b77c-4c9a-9e37-12cc2b5159e7">
      <Text>A beat. The voice drops lower. Intimate. Almost tender.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="39d08f63-4279-44fa-a7b4-63c47c0df5eb">
      <Text>VOICE (V.O.)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="d7368d58-0212-478e-b5e3-0f3a4ce3d5c2">
      <Text>Well then. I guess we know who's going to prison.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Transition" id="47245a5c-b63a-4717-a397-7bb24767e51e">
      <Text>SMASH CUT TO:</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="e50b0a30-523d-44e2-b10f-766602870891">
      <Text>TITLE CARD: THE PLAYBOY</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="5b08510f-42df-4738-a450-45fe1f2fc249">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="2" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>EXT. MIDTOWN MANHATTAN - DUSK</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="f03f24b6-1f07-4275-a0ca-32ef226ab0cb">
      <Text>Aerial shot descending through amber light. The city exhales its Monday. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="ad6ea374-c3b4-43ce-b6ac-c365fd55b146">
      <Text>We push past glass towers reflecting dying sun until we find a black Lincoln Continental crawling through post-rush traffic on Sixth Avenue.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="19f89a35-dd92-4238-bbb6-7924a919a7f4">
      <SceneProperties Length="3 3/8" Page="2" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="EMMANUEL">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="KEVIN">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. TOWN CAR - CONTINUOUS</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="f17df498-6bab-4640-8a0b-6e9d567e0d46">
      <Text>KEVIN McCORT (45), handsome in that careful way that costs money— Brunello Cucinelli sport coat, open collar, exactly three days of stubble cultivated by a barber who charges $175 for "texture"— is mid-sentence on a call. His AirPod Pros are shiny white. Of course.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="9159b6ca-277a-4052-89f4-71d0353d0672">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="a74e58d7-8563-4039-b3c9-baaa63ee5768">
      <Text>(rapid, controlled, the COO voice)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="5af420ab-4c8f-40e3-a6dd-b535e8b26f23">
      <Text>— and tell Chet I want the CFIUS filing locked before the board call Thursday. No, not the summary deck, the actual fucking filing. Redacted. Yes. To his personal. No, I'm not worried about Merkur, I'm worried about optics. Merkur's a forty-billion-dollar German healthcare conglomerate, not a Chinese shell company, I checked all the data myself.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="5d9d7ac2-b4f4-418f-96b8-dd78b3d8c03c">
      <Text>(beat, listening)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="d67650e2-4e68-4550-a017-caa5e8ed663e">
      <Text>It looks real because it is real, it’s not like we're selling patient data to foreigners, Marcus. That's why.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="98f8c4e1-2554-402f-abc2-98b796403a95">
      <Text>He swipes through his phone while talking—Bloomberg, a text from "The Wife" contact listing in his phone, he doesn't open, his own LinkedIn notifications.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="f8491d96-fd4b-4d6c-8d12-8694e3360b9f">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="bac77eec-d218-4124-a263-1cd7cb2087e6">
      <Text>The target's board signed the term sheet forty minutes ago. I countersigned in 15. I snapped that shit, taking a victory lap! We close in eleven days. Eleven. Days. And then? Then I stop being COO of a mid-cap analytics firm and start being COO of the seventh largest biotech data platform in North America and Europe mother fucker!</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="3957f093-09e6-495e-9de2-ad921ce7bb41">
      <Text>(finally smiling)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="4caa1970-8781-4179-8720-94f29d0e7c26">
      <Text>Yeah. Yeah, that's right. Tell the team drinks are on me Friday. The good stuff. Not the Veuve, the Krug.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="2e5c85b4-aac9-49f5-84c9-89c260ff62e5">
      <Text>He ends the call. Exhales. The smile stays— not because he's happy but because he's practiced it.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="60cd1803-be73-40c9-ba2c-f2ef48057e5a">
      <Text>Kevin catches his own reflection in the window, adjusts slightly, then notices the new driver. Not his regular guy.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="9ad21c82-1a89-45a5-abf5-028ea105d141">
      <Text>The driver is EMMANUEL (50s), Haitian, still wearing his formal black jacket even though it's warm. There's gray at his temples. A small Haitian flag air freshener hangs from the mirror alongside a laminated photo of a woman and three children.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="c81fad02-0740-4947-8197-19a560de7ef4">
      <Text>Kevin studies the back of Emmanuel's head the way he studies market conditions. An opportunity.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="badca993-4338-41e1-99fa-6bab1d76e3ee">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="394465d5-4104-4d48-81be-84cbe0b0e9d5">
      <Text>(warm, conspiratorial, leaning forward)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="db34cbfc-01ca-42aa-8a85-d7ea247d894b">
      <Text>Hey. Long day?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="27c2372a-2619-4bb5-b7db-9949ab1287cd">
      <Text>Emmanuel glances in the rearview. Polite but wary. He's been doing this for years.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="3a611151-4185-42ec-8cea-b6023c11c25c">
      <Text>EMMANUEL</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="403d296c-f74c-4c07-a6e5-99da0ae56fd5">
      <Text>Not so bad, sir.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="06486cfb-7cc3-469d-b9d5-fb88d5e087c2">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="a1aad022-d599-4f4c-8a57-150a4da81cda">
      <Text>Kevin. Please. I hate "sir." Makes me feel like my father.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="e9d9be72-9271-44a5-b8ea-92e072f6ae70">
      <Text>(chuckle he definitely practiced once)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="698f98aa-72fe-41ac-a28e-be554048b9f0">
      <Text>What happened to Luis?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="286aecd0-ac27-4b4e-9659-958ce5323b82">
      <Text>EMMANUEL</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="9869da00-4eac-4b86-b8e8-325c8468e796">
      <Text>I don't know any Luis. I am with company only two weeks.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="7af57efd-3dc5-470f-b909-6667110d32fa">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="a99801ac-fd91-495f-8d7d-ba251fad497a">
      <Text>Two weeks. Well, welcome aboard. I'm on your route a lot. UBS Tower to West 84th. You'll get to know me.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="8bfc2885-b689-411e-9640-eff2555f89d8">
      <Text>(beat, genuine attempt at warmth)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="a7976e50-1eba-41e4-93fb-629decdc78e2">
      <Text>I'm easy. Low maintenance. No complaints to dispatch, none of that. What's your name?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="20da7096-f9b1-4aeb-814a-a9d918371391">
      <Text>EMMANUEL</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="c01a8ffb-3fad-4051-acea-d17c5010d5a9">
      <Text>Emmanuel.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="8e8b34a3-2a1e-4b72-9694-55e5008be144">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="90168a26-8c2a-444b-8bf2-16426372a3bb">
      <Text>Manny, got it.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="a6fc056e-919a-4ce1-b63f-5a5bb554cdaa">
      <Text>Emmanuel says nothing. Adjusts his grip on the wheel.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="c4c80d29-fb04-4050-a63d-34aaf7883077">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="7c0d3d07-62b2-4f04-8579-3e2b54011272">
      <Text>You want some music? I don't care. Whatever you're into. Hip-hop, that rap shit, whatever. My daughter's always telling me I need to expand my—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="93838027-1f88-4615-a970-5e34477aa8ed">
      <Text>(gesturing vaguely)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="2a4f31a4-4d9d-4a6d-826d-0ef55e4c3373">
      <Text>— palate. Cultural palate.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="2a724ce8-f519-4c4a-8b90-f3e570f1c1ff">
      <Text>EMMANUEL</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="a81fa71f-10c3-4614-94b6-a516c2d162c8">
      <Text>I am okay with quiet.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="0a9ce127-5583-4e74-acf0-6b87eb9382f1">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="7c8a028a-519a-4258-a3a6-1743853902f6">
      <Text>(laughing, not getting it)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="8540b0f3-f428-465e-b225-88d7ed8b7851">
      <Text>Fair enough. Fair enough. The quiet's nice. Decompress after the chaos, right?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="6b610e60-b462-4955-b698-b94306e21034">
      <Text>Kevin settles back. But he's not done. Can't help himself.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="5ea1ae48-8065-4147-99d6-8364f166d66a">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="2540316d-3ea9-4538-b5a9-4b37a3ecf97d">
      <Text>Where you from originally? If you don't mind.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="218a9ef2-c06d-4e17-9eba-be35e6adfc1e">
      <Text>EMMANUEL</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="fd246fa9-38c1-4a26-8415-c12867097170">
      <Text>(pointing at the flag air freshener)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="d00a4375-fc89-4374-80e6-fb5a7e97506f">
      <Text>Haiti.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="ed84504e-727e-4601-8b30-43c6201c897b">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="d6154300-c054-4741-8f82-be14348dd2a4">
      <Text>Haiti! Beautiful country. Tragic, what happened. The earthquake. Just—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="336a4011-495a-4e31-8414-783f33ddc12e">
      <Text>(shakes his head, practiced empathy)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="55961151-5a81-44ee-96fc-c261fb73d365">
      <Text>We actually donated to that. My company. Well, my previous company. Significant amount. To the relief effort.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="7af61911-d99b-4837-8aae-efd9bee8db93">
      <Text>EMMANUEL</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="e7baea58-709f-4495-b111-0ae41cc508e7">
      <Text>(flat)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="2e9fccfb-719d-44eb-830f-2cc17504f9ef">
      <Text>Thank you.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="49cbb4e7-f758-4313-9f53-a81e0920f50c">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="0aa25c84-f822-4d56-b59c-9a05a098b786">
      <Text>Don't thank me. It's just— you know— basic human decency. We're all in this together, right?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="36385c5a-7935-46d8-8719-8b120dd7c686">
      <Text>A pause. Kevin watches the city slide by.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="e116c17e-8567-4f73-8d9d-535db0bccc67">
      <Text>EMMANUEL</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="4a342626-47c8-49f8-80e6-4234c57f2af1">
      <Text>Thank you.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="f4cb2420-b75c-46f1-8aa6-4896ecbac017">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="636e6fc7-bf2c-4d2c-8b59-73f93139a07c">
      <Text>(settling back, satisfied)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="053b62e0-0432-4c18-aeba-a2a31188c975">
      <Text>Happy to help. I mean that. People helped me when I was coming up. You pay it forward. That's how it works.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="385f93c8-61c4-4070-a5b9-e63b721e7c29">
      <Text>He pulls out his phone again, scrolling. The connection— such as it was— has served its purpose. Kevin has performed his humanity.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="77a99ac9-33fa-4b80-a34e-fb1c36f8968b">
      <Text>Emmanuel watches him in the rearview. His face betrays nothing.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="dfd543cb-5c83-4749-8e51-982aa4eb6d8a">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="a10ce909-1d31-46e9-9bed-2bc810358f9d">
      <Text>(back on phone, to himself)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="28ff8e3d-e688-425b-b3dd-bbc1fdb6ba12">
      <Text>Jesus. Nasdaq's up two percent. Should've stayed in longer.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="ebc6083a-f397-4e71-b1fc-a6fa68432c29">
      <Text>He texts someone. Laughs at his own reply.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="c33170cd-0981-44ae-9263-5689a4c85524">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="5" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>EXT. UPPER WEST SIDE - WEST 84TH STREET - CONTINUOUS</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="8831935d-543a-42d8-97d6-600688b1f753">
      <Text>The car turns onto a tree-lined block between Central Park West and Columbus. Brownstones worth eight, ten, twenty million dollars hide behind wrought iron gates. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="ab343b86-763e-4f37-b245-68140c140ccd">
      <Text>The McCort residence is a four-story Greek Revival townhouse, white-painted brick, black shutters. Immaculate planters. A brass "84" by the door.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="7baeb118-f2db-4f8e-ab29-e74dd82001a7">
      <Text>Old money taste. New money funding.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="918a8a6b-b217-4e85-9c25-8dd525c74f00">
      <SceneProperties Length="3/8" Page="6" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="EMMANUEL">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="KEVIN">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. TOWN CAR - CONTINUOUS</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="3b4e7955-6458-44af-a35b-4d8887f57127">
      <Text>Kevin gathers himself. Jacket adjustment. Quick check of teeth in phone camera.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="cffbe814-31bd-47b7-939d-a508f471fab5">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="04446ab9-5989-4c66-b8b2-dd568a323e84">
      <Text>(punching a twenty into the tip app)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="3beaa9cd-5121-4ffa-b3df-85542307497f">
      <Text>Beautiful. You have a good night, Manny. And I meant what I said. About your son. Ur... or the earthquake thing.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="dad40375-2bb1-4e7d-8798-9656950a9a0b">
      <Text>EMMANUEL</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="692162e2-8930-416c-b727-3826f4d7328c">
      <Text>(same flat tone)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="a895ca91-b6a6-448e-bcc5-288f5844dd66">
      <Text>Thank you, sir. Kevin.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="38b77add-0230-414e-bf27-748949e6eba2">
      <Text>Kevin steps out.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="92ea34be-224c-4e07-b84b-bf2d4babf3e6">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="6" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>EXT. MCCORT TOWNHOUSE - CONTINUOUS</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="9d771eb8-c9ce-4411-8f54-6cd0a9e4891d">
      <Text>Kevin approaches the front door. Pauses.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d8ed5ef0-0585-45fb-98e3-353666f60787">
      <Text>The doorman's station is empty. Odd.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="8dc8c00c-7476-4e58-8b1f-1210cee8a15b">
      <Text>Kevin tries the outer door. It's unlocked. Odder.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="95301827-bb81-435f-9e78-3daf60eabd8a">
      <Text>He enters the foyer.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="a8f63bc1-b086-4954-9579-3d6b0683290c">
      <SceneProperties Length="1" Page="6" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="BILL">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="KEVIN">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. MCCORT TOWNHOUSE - FOYER - CONTINUOUS</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="f542434f-13e2-476d-a75d-e4696605099f">
      <Text>Italian marble. Fresh lilies on a reclaimed-wood console table that cost more than Emmanuel makes in two months. A framed black-and-white photograph of the family on a Hamptons beach, professionally shot, professionally casual.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="a428de68-650c-45d4-8932-ae0765931090">
      <Text>The elevator DINGS.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="dd794619-7977-49e7-8406-acd580985d19">
      <Text>BILL (60s), doorman uniform ruffled, a former NYPD beat cop who has been with the McCorts for eleven years, steps out. He's adjusting his tie. Tucking in his shirt. His face is flushed.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="e8fddd66-174a-4f7c-a193-9ea905366f9c">
      <Text>BILL</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="7d1e46dd-95a7-4d4c-bab0-7b26b62a3e89">
      <Text>(startled)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="b154cb72-2b5a-4aa8-8e9d-cac3ccc124d3">
      <Text>Mr. McCort! Sorry, I was just— helping Mrs. McCort with some groceries. In the kitchen.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="7da003d6-8a04-403b-a960-19c9b2e63009">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="dc288b6a-1b5e-48a7-b8c6-a6629b864282">
      <Text>(already scrolling his phone)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="a1ac6389-1dc7-46a9-81db-8cd6873bf1ef">
      <Text>No worries, Bill. Long day?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="714a99e7-0ac9-45a7-b08d-b4e1131febeb">
      <Text>BILL</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="14760d85-8475-4c49-a614-07fb5fa21995">
      <Text>(swallowing)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="23655cae-ef88-4798-a902-60ace6142a41">
      <Text>Just the usual, sir.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="56ce1bbb-becc-4dc4-8107-9baa40d48c9b">
      <Text>Kevin moves past him toward the elevator, doesn't notice:</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="6c17b9a5-0e90-4cf0-a91a-001022e733cf">
      <Text>Bill's belt is undone.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="b353edcf-1153-479e-9d91-13e5d64bab48">
      <Text>And his lipstick-smudged collar is inexpertly tucked.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="081e34e4-454e-4932-8e44-29ebaf354609">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="33aa7113-42ec-4770-be0d-e8a275b945a0">
      <Text>(stepping into elevator)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="f2d8d15c-2506-45b0-86fa-d52b6433b47f">
      <Text>Dinner in twenty, right?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="c84dee0f-4ba6-4c4c-8859-4dc247076cb2">
      <Text>BILL</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="278c623a-edcf-4fc4-9678-2a01d28c3d6c">
      <Text>I believe so, sir. Mrs. McCort is preparing.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="d8beceb9-0f57-4c7d-92dd-00b46570a6c0">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="5301cfc3-1fba-4aac-b2f7-c63a9fc097c1">
      <Text>(to himself, pleased)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="70530c12-ed3d-4523-854e-77fbdf12cf59">
      <Text>Family dinner. Keeps us grounded.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="867c4c98-7b02-40f8-b18a-281f86c8e78b">
      <Text>The elevator doors close on Kevin's self-satisfied smile.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="b61593f2-813a-49f9-8c77-28ddcadadeba">
      <Text>Bill exhales. Wipes his mouth.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="1284d133-dee8-414c-ba06-f0ac4d76eb9a">
      <SceneProperties Length="4/8" Page="7" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="KEVIN">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. MCCORT TOWNHOUSE - ELEVATOR - CONTINUOUS</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="39d18057-22be-4e38-b0d0-f02d5995682b">
      <Text>Kevin alone with his reflection in the brass elevator doors.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="6d46e249-a521-4e74-925b-12065636a13f">
      <Text>He straightens his posture. Adjusts the expression. Becomes the version of himself his family is supposed to see: calm, present, paternal.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="0b7512fc-9a10-43e8-b294-a41967fa07c9">
      <Text>The performance of a man performing competence at the performance of fatherhood.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="11464a9b-c76c-47ad-82d2-0b371fb0423a">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="e92fee93-88b5-4038-a315-757138e5f2b5">
      <Text>(under his breath, mantra)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="ec6b6fae-590f-429b-807c-db8cf4b65c58">
      <Text>Whether in an advantageous position or a disadvantageous one... the opposite state should always be present to your mind.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="6232214c-02da-4b8a-94e6-bec089d5307b">
      <Text>He takes a breath. Satisfied. A man who has read Sun Tzu and understood nothing.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="32be8419-9a2a-404f-984c-4cd397bcab32">
      <Text>The doors open.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="ab036240-d9c4-4c77-8e72-ec7e317ac9ba">
      <SceneProperties Length="3 1/8" Page="8" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="JAMIE">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="JANET">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="JAZ">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="KEVIN">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. MCCORT TOWNHOUSE - MAIN FLOOR - CONTINUOUS</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="763302cc-7f62-4d69-9570-36296510afa4">
      <Text>An open floor plan that cost $1,500,000 to renovate into existence. The kitchen gleams. JANET McCORT (43) stands at an island of white marble, arranging takeout containers into serving dishes. The deception of home cooking.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="747aa1b3-c619-4225-bcc5-3eb79398c5dd">
      <Text>She's in yoga pants and a cashmere wrap. Hair perfect. Skin perfect. The kind of beauty that looks effortless and costs $10,000 a month to maintain.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="7d62d2bc-7bea-4307-854b-89c077daf6d1">
      <Text>She looks up. Smiles. The smile is perfect too.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="3d3c15c8-02bb-430f-bda5-347538037fc8">
      <Text>JANET</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="fd6eb751-0442-4cf9-80a4-cc53ec76bf3c">
      <Text>You're early.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="c402979d-d52a-4305-822b-722d6e09357e">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="24e21924-20fa-4cb0-a861-610347c16d03">
      <Text>Closed the Merkur deal. Couldn't focus on anything else, so I bailed.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="13f0f943-51d5-4093-81f4-7e05155137fc">
      <Text>He crosses to her. Kisses her cheek. Doesn't notice that her breath is slightly elevated. Or that her lips are freshly applied.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="b15e48c0-9391-4536-98cd-98ff7c2a0b0f">
      <Text>JANET</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="1ce51370-0a0c-4101-8163-faeffaac8aba">
      <Text>Congratulations. That's huge.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="7d57f7a4-7fc4-4a6d-9663-13df86b22faa">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="201c8d3d-793d-47c3-80e6-7c77287a1610">
      <Text>It's not nothing.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="6457c124-fc53-47c8-a884-79dbc13c58f2">
      <Text>(surveying the "cooking")</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="5bb8dc88-9fd4-46af-98b0-df334c332091">
      <Text>Smells good. What are we having?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="4ca13d6d-b004-4150-b6db-c2ed3e861bd2">
      <Text>JANET</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="e3e0d789-7260-43cf-98a4-96a7d7a8ea9d">
      <Text>That lemon chicken you like. From Épicerie.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="3aeb2014-f99f-4b27-b1fb-bde9c08cfe89">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="b64faddb-eb44-4816-b255-0997e560f262">
      <Text>You're too good to me.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="c294ccf6-a96e-4dc6-8e89-a6119850d3e0">
      <Text>JANET</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="6381f8cf-0571-4dea-a300-b4b883509113">
      <Text>(small smile, loaded)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="25daca55-6cd6-4356-a58a-adb77bec60e2">
      <Text>I know.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="9f0d69e5-7ce7-48ac-a558-03fe3a8b664f">
      <Text>Kevin looks at his Patek Nautilus. the time is now.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="10aae26b-00a5-4142-a86d-46d6c65b4587">
      <Text>And as if on cue, we HEAR, from upstairs, a DOOR SLAM.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="eed8a31e-03ec-468c-902b-60c9451019e1">
      <Text>Then FOOTSTEPS. Heavy. Annoyed.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="32d05b53-c2e4-4ed1-aa69-2d607f27f265">
      <Text>JAZMINE (JAZ) McCORT (18) descends the stairs. Long chestnut hair, glossy and straight, frames a face that belongs on a Noxzema commercial. Blue eyes burn like sapphires.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="5ba09a76-2094-4ee2-a87f-920e555de058">
      <Text>She's wearing a vintage Princeton crew neck—her father's alma mater, the implication clear—and high-waisted jeans that manage to look both effortless and expensive. Small gold studs in her ears. A delicate cross necklace her grandmother gave her at confirmation.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d44ab7a8-e4e1-49f6-b036-7593840ad748">
      <Text>She is, by any measure, the kind of daughter other parents reference when disappointed in their own children.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="a0143844-1de6-4945-8622-df95de93c24f">
      <Text>She looks like an admissions brochure.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="94041fd3-ba26-412e-9d51-d6209e57e1ca">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="098b1680-72e4-4446-9c5e-f9c6b62d042c">
      <Text>(dead voice, perfect diction)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="066a8034-fb7b-46e2-b51d-f4ea65e0163e">
      <Text>Hey Dad. Congrats on the acquisition.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="1b2cceae-6315-4ad5-a09d-c6da2804dbc9">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="207176bd-9007-4195-b489-295564916b3f">
      <Text>(brightening)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="35de4962-ba16-4991-b303-f83b3b4bad89">
      <Text>You saw the news?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="6e1b867e-31ee-4e9b-88a1-a2ff490f4776">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="9c00a01a-c4cb-4dc3-b520-fc40c7cf08c0">
      <Text>LinkedIn notification.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="3c0c197a-934d-4553-bed3-2a00fbaa3000">
      <Text>(doesn't look up from phone)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="a568a96a-ba46-43bf-8029-bedf4b8458b7">
      <Text>You posted about it.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="c2a77f5d-ebea-4798-8b69-bf95298da333">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="9190ed27-9d46-4702-bd9f-be181db9ea47">
      <Text>Right. Yes. Building the brand.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="493d9d73-1a33-4f5a-acbe-e304dfefd5c2">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="6b552a24-e4f5-4f29-adf3-74ece07e0c8f">
      <Text>How was school?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="11decaad-47f5-4aa4-b405-e4b38d88d1c8">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="91ff049f-9fd1-40f3-8f66-734f00e799db">
      <Text>Educational.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="78d43213-60fe-4a51-a776-0ff53beaea8f">
      <Text>JAMIE McCORT (14) appears at the top of the stairs. Pale, thin, watching everything like he's recording it for later analysis. Which he is.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="6931fc1e-ca26-472a-a80e-65999fbba687">
      <Text>JAMIE</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="5a4bd2a3-7b7b-44e0-b4c5-5267cd83e7ed">
      <Text>(descending)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="5292481b-fc70-4fba-a78d-180d7a98fcb2">
      <Text>Merkur's data architecture is pre-pandemic legacy. You're going to have integration issues with your AWS stack.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="8f999dc8-5ac9-4f15-bd4f-3dcc0d204f66">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="01b8fc60-a49f-47f1-89ba-5a9173c19da9">
      <Text>(chuckling, looking at Janet)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="b74397c3-b0f5-4f7b-be5e-552393ba73bf">
      <Text>And who says all those video games will rot your brains.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="2fb93b6f-8e40-4675-bbe2-f2c90dd40352">
      <Text>JAMIE</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="d855b077-8f88-4799-8873-1b8bd395804b">
      <Text>(rolling his eyes)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="3c5c76d3-d59b-465f-a0af-0c1c0ed5217c">
      <Text>I'm not wrong.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="a80ae4b9-205b-4b31-8bc6-de8ac274774b">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="b30e2694-289a-4fd5-8b7c-2dd0b6046d3f">
      <Text>Don’t you worry your little head about it kiddo. Your old man’s a slayer.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="108b4438-cccb-4357-975e-ebc7db72e78f">
      <Text>Kevin's smile flickers. Just for a moment. Then:</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="09b9d323-ee0e-4ee1-9643-526929a17648">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="38540c84-b00b-4018-a78a-26b458c40e61">
      <Text>How’re the hot chick prospects. Maybe get out in the sun this week, bud? Huh?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="77c67de5-d147-49c6-a810-e6b56fb02b1d">
      <Text>He turns to the table, where Janet is setting out the hidden takeout.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="9864de95-b160-4d94-a00c-c0a0c0424dde">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="18fa0651-cb34-4e2b-b345-f9c5745f71f6">
      <Text>Alright. Family dinner. Let's do this.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="e09d445b-5e58-426b-a6ec-95800899625a">
      <Text>They gather. Four people who share a name and an address. Nothing else.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="ae5e4d6f-0111-4881-b234-70d846d68f85">
      <Text>Kevin</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="ae2ee9dd-0c38-4a6b-99b4-9c76f321cb72">
      <Text>So Jazzy? How’s that boyfriend treating you? Cole, Colby, Carl... right? He’s not trying to pull anything with you, right?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="f9174980-a633-4043-899f-f3dfc39c07b8">
      <Text>(trying to remember)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="052bc2df-7fcd-419b-a866-486d662de19b">
      <Text>We had a decent chat over dinner.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="3052a439-0f0e-4a4d-a3fe-e0e8072f5128">
      <Text>A Norman Rockwell painting if Rockwell had been deeply ironic.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="e5eda116-3f0e-44ee-84d9-0bf2da816801">
      <Text>Janet</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="87bc9703-788e-485e-b7b0-a1f84211d417">
      <Text>I always liked him. Sweet boy, </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="1d8abe79-8185-46ef-9471-4132480f8116">
      <Text>(conspiratorial with Jaz)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="7151d446-3159-4c41-be12-f11ba3bdc864">
      <Text>Cute for sure... Right?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="148b52c3-add8-499c-86e0-1a79adfa7b4f">
      <Text>Jaz</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="eb0ea3e2-f3bb-426f-bf63-cfc00f840e40">
      <Text>(not at all interested in any of this)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="1a308f24-f139-4391-9c26-f4d840ae2f78">
      <Text>We broke up right after you met him.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="901561b0-e141-4274-86d8-780ac27a5e05">
      <Text>Candles. Cloth napkins. Bone china.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="dc22a399-bd1f-4f53-a923-f0cb13d019ad">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="218f5906-1aa3-484b-b2a8-1a40b8db5fdd">
      <Text>Oh, wasn’t that like last week?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="b9d8767f-1c5b-44c2-812f-243adaa20b07">
      <Text>Four masks, expertly worn.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="fdf25182-5c2d-4644-a73b-0d9aeb167eb4">
      <Text>jAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="7d1069d8-4f58-4f77-8896-e0bf99cf18bd">
      <Text>2 years ago.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="5cfa1a1f-095f-4cb8-a088-272b82bde79f">
      <Text>They eat.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="0a2b28b0-177e-4b1a-b9af-8764c1bcaa50">
      <SceneProperties Length="3 4/8" Page="11" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="JANET">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="JAZ">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="KEVIN">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. MCCORT TOWNHOUSE - KITCHEN - LATER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d5949c59-7897-4682-8b03-75f25352a823">
      <Text>The dinner detritus. Plates smeared with the remains of "homemade" lemon chicken. Wine glasses. A $400 candle burning down. JANET stands at the sink, looking at the pile of dishes, then down at her hands. Her nails are immaculate— a fresh gel manicure, that specific shade of ballet pink that costs $180 at the salon on Columbus because they use "Japanese technique." She picks up a plate. Considers it. Sets it back down.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="9a9e2ed7-adcb-4240-907a-b543777f1232">
      <Text>JANET</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="aa00299e-e745-481e-a1f9-473965eda73f">
      <Text>Maria can do these in the morning.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="34a3de2d-87d9-4e0c-8091-19570b2eacbf">
      <Text>She dries her hands on a monogrammed towel, satisfied with the decision. KEVIN enters from the dining room, loosening his collar, carrying his wine glass like a prop in a photo shoot about successful men relaxing.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="7c126dd1-fef0-4247-aa16-371a57c4fe3c">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="e9ecc529-6446-4d80-9b96-10834a70268e">
      <Text>Kids are upstairs?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="574b42f4-2340-4f92-aab1-c7bffb5c5df2">
      <Text>JANET</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="76673f88-73a7-4497-a73a-ce2790f2ce57">
      <Text>Jamie's in his cave. Jaz is studying.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="325b64ac-a3fc-4b49-8f9c-ca6bf8d9d714">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="400a1c5e-3bdf-47c4-8806-4e371c3934da">
      <Text>Good. Good.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="ab28f409-d6cb-4f62-a5f9-4c5c9a38c8eb">
      <Text>He leans against the island, watching her. That look husbands give when they think they're about to deliver good news.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="763084e9-d97f-4818-ac9e-206dfb24791b">
      <Text>JANET</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="0f94cea7-e103-46c8-953d-0f22f08befa9">
      <Text>What.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="313f014a-1254-48e3-8e4c-169c086ccdd2">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="55cc2fb7-b9b2-4e0e-8ea7-09e9022694ab">
      <Text>So. Chet called me after the term sheet signed.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="d6ee06fb-c66e-4861-8051-b74aaad6c33d">
      <Text>JANET</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="45ffc7b3-c36a-4c65-aa30-d42605c2b5a0">
      <Text>(carefully neutral)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="4404f71b-d1a2-4c1d-a962-bc5d438be98f">
      <Text>Did he.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="d670f674-243c-41cb-bbed-598983f4d94c">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="c4701021-22a3-4712-a690-6b8f4f42cc58">
      <Text>Wants to celebrate. Once we close. He's taking the boat out to Sag Harbor, wants us there for the weekend. You, me, him, Muffy—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="f6b0b234-a340-4d18-b4bc-71ebfabc0cd7">
      <Text>JANET</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="552c6aa5-1250-468e-ba87-5311a9ac385d">
      <Text>Her name is Morgan.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="1103ba98-c6c5-4a9f-857e-3e74ce2e12b9">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="b664aeca-6523-4185-b6e4-d0149c9ed0bf">
      <Text>Right. Morgan. Whatever. Point is, he was very... adamant. That you come.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="5befd6c2-4bab-4f36-8be5-f5fb360258e7">
      <Text>Janet turns to face him fully, her expression perfectly calibrated.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="8533d648-59ff-48cc-b037-894a614247e7">
      <Text>JANET</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="5d30924d-de8e-4134-8a8e-823713fd4081">
      <Text>Was he.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="85d27e17-a98f-4c06-96a5-1abd9bbcd597">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="531c6852-7913-4f80-81f4-3d22ba685762">
      <Text>(grinning, conspiratorial)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="4bd5b000-cee5-427c-863b-1d79cb532d72">
      <Text>You know, I think Chet's always had a little thing for you. Ever since Princeton. I think he's still kicking himself that you went home with me that night and not him.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="eac16955-b418-432a-a7ab-09605461caec">
      <Text>A beat. Janet's face doesn't change, but something behind her eyes does. A flicker. Kevin doesn't notice.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="1bb5a2e3-2ae8-4eff-bfcf-952bfc5669d1">
      <Text>JANET</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="b2e71377-14dd-4ca0-ae0c-21dbc046da89">
      <Text>(light, easy)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="8ed6abc4-ad45-4f78-9c06-43ede88d03d1">
      <Text>You think so?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="7ba14ecd-7f24-4493-a211-a9fc3c521535">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="13f6a47e-2ce5-40df-9db8-44fc391113cd">
      <Text>Oh, come on. The way he looks at you? At every corporate retreat? I'm not blind.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="c7ef42d4-7d58-4dad-bd13-f255036b9d2d">
      <Text>(chuckling)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="f34e5862-bc5a-4832-8720-d0805629b2b4">
      <Text>He even said—and I quote—"Make sure Janet goes bikini shopping with Morgan before." Like that's subtle.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="63cb8d97-2a71-4878-a4dd-a4569dfbd2ee">
      <Text>JANET</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="5e80ebc4-2f5b-447b-b997-2b0c54f063ec">
      <Text>How thoughtful of him.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="f81f41ea-baf5-476e-812f-9894b9b12e6b">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="52ffd46b-78b4-4033-8842-df58686f84b2">
      <Text>Hey, I'm not complaining. You should go. Get something nice. Something that makes Chet realize what he missed out on.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="c50d0f4f-3eb0-40a9-bc34-2aed4fb47916">
      <Text>(winking)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="57420cf8-7ba1-431c-a5f6-fc01ed13e0d5">
      <Text>Remind him who won.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="dd496dd0-61a2-4c74-8f20-230cb448613e">
      <Text>Janet smiles. It's a beautiful smile. Perfectly constructed.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="a2e81126-f980-4e66-bd07-ffb6349b46ac">
      <Text>JANET</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="fa3d5989-6a6a-4955-9100-89aaee710b24">
      <Text>I'll call Morgan tomorrow. Set something up.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="f35ec4d9-42d1-405f-9584-68e27ff8e8cb">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="0d6216e2-8b07-493f-885f-888911429525">
      <Text>That's my girl.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="849d3503-40a7-4818-a815-1c2932122cd8">
      <Text>He kisses her forehead. The kiss of a man who has never once suspected he doesn't have the full picture. He tops off his wine, heads toward the living room.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="3b3a5d83-26a6-4e87-bd43-2059af210d93">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="7f9cf2b7-435e-4d71-9b94-3c37713e746c">
      <Text>I'm going to catch the market wrap-up. Join me?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="9dcc8e10-4bb1-431c-9b87-4195a906efdb">
      <Text>JANET</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="16022b56-ed15-4883-8b40-3dff2bc691a2">
      <Text>In a minute.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="0f2e4e44-4ae0-42f8-884e-f7bac8895e6a">
      <Text>He exits. Janet stays. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="fbcef8ca-433d-49df-b8f8-ccacaf79d462">
      <Text>Alone with the dishes she won't wash. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="ea9de6f6-f2b8-480c-a4fb-6e6583f80f46">
      <Text>She pulls out her phone, scrolls to a text thread with no name—just initials: C.M. The last message, from two hours ago: no text, just a photo an extremely large hairy cock.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="269f38a1-b380-46f3-ae90-0e5549bd53bb">
      <Text>She types nothing. Just stares at it. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="4319dd08-a0d5-4588-a3c0-c68347fa83c5">
      <Text>FOOTSTEPS on the stairs. Janet pockets the phone in one fluid motion. JAZ bounces into the kitchen—full ponytail swinging, Princeton sweatshirt, a textbook tucked under her arm. She's carrying a thermos.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="91518563-cf45-415f-b98b-56057f5c6eb7">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="8383aa34-912f-48b9-9e02-1abd726097b7">
      <Text>Hey. Just grabbing some tea for the long haul.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="21c4c686-a334-4072-841e-7ebbbd003577">
      <Text>JANET</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="e0fbe91d-d6d5-4db5-b356-772c6807385b">
      <Text>What's the test?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="91a909a4-752f-455a-bcf3-e5e3b715a7c7">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="eb19a31f-056c-4ce7-a083-1abe0190a6e6">
      <Text>Organic chemistry. It's brutal. Like, legitimately evil. I'll probably be up until two.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="0e8a5b61-f5a6-4a88-a288-9d85753e3b62">
      <Text>JANET</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="8fb92d02-fd4b-42e7-ab1b-96723ac34a85">
      <Text>Do you need anything? I can have Maria bring something up—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="b53db9ae-9b01-42b5-b1e9-a23dc4ebbc3c">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="a9cc2e74-d89d-4762-b243-9ac001a5fd1f">
      <Text>I'm good. Seriously. Just need to lock in.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="a880a9d4-98cb-4a36-8acf-64e7612237bc">
      <Text>(heading out, turning back)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="7bc68e50-3c3a-4f14-bab1-4973baf94880">
      <Text>Don't let Dad knock on my door to say goodnight, okay? Once I'm in the zone, I can't break focus.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="5dbc4cf9-f2a1-4a63-a22d-6bbc8236713a">
      <Text>JANET</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="1374eaee-972e-44e2-a76b-bf8d416bc615">
      <Text>I'll guard the perimeter.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="c274be2a-4eb7-4076-bc3c-09cb792e53ee">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="e7cc3607-12c8-4b13-9add-e0e008fa255a">
      <Text>(smiling, the good daughter)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="62a6c9b4-ad01-4872-99b2-5e6d67ede37c">
      <Text>You're the best.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="5aef5dfe-2254-4f30-8d79-d9638f691039">
      <Text>She disappears up the stairs. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="759484f2-8532-44a9-8ba1-17389375ec8f">
      <Text>Janet listens to her footsteps fade. Then hears, faintly, JAZ'S BEDROOM DOOR CLOSE. And LOCK. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="166f6ff4-b05f-4ad2-a13c-8b93f3f4ccee">
      <Text>Janet looks at the ceiling. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="9b09f6c1-0647-4986-aeb4-121c28a7891a">
      <Text>A mother who knows that "organic chemistry" doesn’t really require a dead bolt. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="9313c95b-5369-433c-b5ff-0952455f4e0c">
      <Text>But asking would require caring. And caring would require knowing. And knowing would require... everything to change. She picks up her wine glass instead.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="4e75dc47-21e6-4d07-9904-e47684deb93e">
      <Text>JANET</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="321389b1-c041-4d32-b342-f913883142e6">
      <Text>(to no one)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="21174a30-5427-4621-bc6e-b3dddec2ee83">
      <Text>Goodnight, sweetheart.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="f5ddaefd-91aa-40b5-9927-dc3a91da1922">
      <SceneProperties Length="4" Page="14" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="CNBC ANCHOR">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="JANET">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="KEVIN">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. MCCORT TOWNHOUSE - MASTER SUITE - NIGHT</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="abc0061d-9775-404b-80c1-545d5f21d50d">
      <Text>The room is a spread from Architectural Digest that was actually in Architectural Digest. California king with a headboard that cost more than a car. Automated blackout shades. A sitting area no one sits in. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="097d3ae4-02f2-4fe2-8749-e6c3903d1076">
      <Text>And dominating the wall opposite the bed: an 85-inch Samsung that probably has a name like "The Wall" or "Infinity" or something else designed to make men feel feelings. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="9ffc6ddf-579c-4b98-906b-186a5e21e7d4">
      <Text>KEVIN is propped against six pillows, still in his dress shirt—unbuttoned now, sleeves rolled, the Patek gleaming on his wrist. His third glass of Caymus sits on the nightstand. On screen, a CNBC anchor is breathlessly recapping the day's market movements.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="3a182f9c-2b8a-4e7c-923d-3bfa306992ba">
      <Text>CNBC ANCHOR (V.O.)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="2c7612a8-d985-4672-a7f5-2de5b3497dec">
      <Text>—and the biotech sector led gains today, with MedAnalytic Systems up four percent on news of their pending Merkur acquisition—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="7f03cbbe-7258-47cd-8388-aff8bfc047b6">
      <Text>Kevin points the remote at the screen like he's conducting.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="1f2c8fbb-c513-4b60-a506-45ace63b11f1">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="8126b9ac-d0d9-4784-bcc3-73950a9e0fbc">
      <Text>(to himself)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="4c4d2be5-a6ef-4a80-8832-9d2a1860d2f7">
      <Text>That's right. That's goddamn right.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="bc2a2ef0-426c-456d-8c21-61d8bbccedfc">
      <Text>The bathroom door opens. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="2c268bd1-664d-4e79-a045-8b713a21c6ce">
      <Text>JANET emerges. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d49ad526-017f-43ac-9d6b-c55c76b01280">
      <Text>She's wearing a La Perla negligee—black silk, hand-embroidered lace, the kind of thing that comes in a box with tissue paper and costs what some people pay in rent. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="67da7059-49d4-4ea9-8b82-1d3ec114d4f5">
      <Text>Her body is a testament to five days a week with a trainer who charges $300 an hour. Everything is exactly where it should be. More than where it should be. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="306885b6-ba50-4169-a381-45bda3f1c9d6">
      <Text>She's backlit by the bathroom light. It's a deliberate entrance. A woman who knows her angles. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="1bf31ae7-feaa-4829-a17c-6f1a4b13016d">
      <Text>She moves to the foot of the bed. Directly between Kevin and the television. Kevin leans slightly to the left to see around her.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="2a9d54f5-a7fe-448f-a24e-3db9fd66530a">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="34e59279-31bf-47bb-ac29-c1473f517192">
      <Text>(distracted)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="9c602e7a-2e38-4b0e-8e95-95192d8407cf">
      <Text>Hey. Kids settled?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="f61ce9c5-69a3-4581-b775-164708f23ad8">
      <Text>JANET</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="260fc252-032e-44c3-833d-9accd5f0594a">
      <Text>Jazzy's locked in her room. Won't come out unless the house is on fire. Some chemistry nightmare.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="a522a7bb-b9ab-4a7a-97d5-626604c91eca">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="a9c41665-cc03-40c0-b38b-d3de63e4f5fa">
      <Text>Good kid.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="80206623-ee4a-4675-8c49-f3ad07ce4b8a">
      <Text>JANET</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="f9216fbc-cec7-494b-93f1-41e79b63a6ed">
      <Text>And Jamie has a new... internet thing. Some obsession. He's in his world.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="75319efd-90c0-4a5f-b005-7a453be4b265">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="a9565abe-08f7-4696-a4fa-2dc5a37f4708">
      <Text>That's my boy. Future CTO.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="e101c3f6-b46d-4e7a-84a6-b7f6138d11ca">
      <Text>He leans the other way. Still trying to see the screen.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="ca6b9671-20dc-4a09-9f2f-f6fa86f7fe03">
      <Text>CNBC ANCHOR (V.O.)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="9273c4a7-3826-4db2-a795-991414383de3">
      <Text>—analysts are calling it one of the most significant data platform consolidations of the year—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d862810b-d986-4108-8ab4-5a3601337da8">
      <Text>Janet takes a step closer. She's now fully blocking the television. The silk catches the light from the screen, shimmering.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="b108c38f-4410-428e-bcaa-6b8f89b54651">
      <Text>JANET</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="84b455d3-b779-4b9a-a781-491c84189d8e">
      <Text>So we have the whole night to ourselves.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="77132e8f-c3d7-40a0-887d-350730686841">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="2cad8902-6b6c-4f68-a4c2-d66f94172874">
      <Text>Mmhmm.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="cfd1e6ef-4a86-4584-8cfa-7a4e52d8dac2">
      <Text>He's not looking at her. He's looking at the slice of screen visible past her left hip.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="ef0d5bff-6e93-4256-b256-db3e6a193362">
      <Text>JANET</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="7f1bb1fc-fa14-46ab-90e3-0a837cc1ba0c">
      <Text>Kevin.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="d6905376-8891-4f00-8026-0ac3c09a6b67">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="34a711b9-f035-4a9a-a801-ecf4109b9373">
      <Text>(eyes still on TV)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="e3594b7b-caf9-49b0-a921-14412cb430cd">
      <Text>Yeah, babe. One sec. They're about to do the sector breakdown.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="8f8944ea-6da6-49a3-a9d5-84fab52f9f25">
      <Text>Janet stands there. A $2,000 negligee. A body that men have risked careers for. A woman who spent forty-five minutes getting ready for this moment. And her husband is watching a graph.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="b1f86890-a741-4992-87aa-a06e13f178d6">
      <Text>JANET</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="4a990305-ad5f-4d27-b05a-8919b42b837b">
      <Text>(carefully)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="8d7855a0-ce88-48f2-a437-cab81879fc16">
      <Text>I thought maybe we could... celebrate. The Merkur thing.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="cc852c35-781e-40fb-8546-09e15708df63">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="9932cdc2-649c-43f6-804d-90fab57c0471">
      <Text>Huh? Uh, yeah. We will. Weekend on Chet's boat, remember?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="1046b544-4c4d-4e57-9c36-828740fdd82d">
      <Text>Kevin still trying to looks around her. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="31f6c91f-c02a-4abe-8df0-7864524471bf">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="dac404d3-b1cf-4c89-8caa-e62f214acd3c">
      <Text>(still glancing at the TV)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="1a6cea40-0db1-48ae-b302-6439ff9749ee">
      <Text>I want to hit the gym early tomorrow. Rodriguez is opening the floor at five-thirty for me and I told him I'd be there. Big day ahead. Lots of pre-close coordination.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="c0678f31-71a2-4458-95f4-465a365aeeae">
      <Text>JANET</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="a262b97f-eaae-42f4-b646-5fbe2476fb28">
      <Text>(flat)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="5a6c3e87-973f-44d9-a4b2-0f5c50640d5c">
      <Text>Right. Big day.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="35312102-d82e-4e73-a467-559bba1445c7">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="462c61e6-3b7a-43a4-8e64-1a0ba3b06502">
      <Text>You look great, by the way. Is that new?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="e769040a-fe8c-4c96-8afb-295f5f39a8e7">
      <Text>His eyes never came off the screen.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="78305e82-0630-405c-8731-564ca8184f7d">
      <Text>JANET</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="1054feb5-88aa-4a00-8ad0-f7b49ba12be5">
      <Text>Six months ago. Your birthday.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="b1f33957-6f19-46eb-af9c-832bbbd44237">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="afe94120-cfa7-4009-8eb9-cf8b59142cba">
      <Text>Right, right. I remember.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="8829b500-f70c-4ea7-8c8c-d27a1fc1d0d5">
      <Text>He doesn't remember. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="c357166f-7dc7-4e12-934d-116fe5f09e04">
      <Text>The market wrap-up ends. A commercial for wealth management services begins—a silver-haired man walking on a beach with his perfect family, text on screen reading: "What matters most?" </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="8b5c09ee-477f-4bc3-9353-12997501ec30">
      <Text>Kevin kills the TV.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="deeca0b8-b83b-4f83-ad34-ee41806d6717">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="848a14c1-fd40-4434-a8f8-a314383b43db">
      <Text>(yawning, satisfied)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="e36c84e1-7b7a-4376-be7d-d99a8f05eff7">
      <Text>God, what a day. What a day.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="7f97b64f-92ad-4782-971c-8b12590ed27d">
      <Text>He sets his wine glass down, still half dressed on top of the covers.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="9664a682-d3b8-45f1-a679-6fde5b2c5a8b">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="613072bd-aa8c-48ca-a385-a0fffae842f5">
      <Text>You coming to bed?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="a4aed861-8bd3-4340-a486-553280f3a129">
      <Text>JANET</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="c17ae1d6-19df-4aab-84ce-013b9ecedcee">
      <Text>In a minute.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="3e432087-06e0-4e9d-91cc-b1f176636d91">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="49f5580d-deb5-4d3d-ac65-e2e8bfa111d5">
      <Text>(eyes already closing)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="380c3145-d4bb-42b4-b77a-209ccfdd9e8c">
      <Text>Love you, babe. Big week ahead. Gonna conquer the world.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="0f8dc497-3d36-456d-acf1-6f40be32a986">
      <Text>JANET</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="ffa93471-49de-40f3-b48f-7f0afbf72626">
      <Text>I know you will.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="04c6efa4-14e1-490b-8235-13f337d4199a">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="fc88f0d6-1ee6-4979-a6da-b30fc9adc1c9">
      <Text>(murmuring, fading)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="1d3fef5f-fc16-48d7-bdc2-d784344d4de8">
      <Text>We're really doing it. The dream. All of it...</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="781ce84d-f6e8-40c9-ab95-e8f0c8a51074">
      <Text>And like that, he's out. The sleep of the righteous. The sleep of a man who has never once questioned whether he's enough. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="cd2760bb-adab-4fa1-8325-15ba8663698c">
      <Text>Janet stands at the foot of the bed in her $2,000 silk, watching her husband snore. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="fab7246b-4dcd-47f8-915e-b5ea09ddbd5d">
      <Text>Her phone buzzes on the vanity. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="f15e6bed-cb56-44da-955e-3b826c49c5f8">
      <Text>She walks over. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="4d64a395-67f9-48d5-9e7f-ce9281c278f7">
      <Text>Looks at the screen. C.M.: "Still up?" </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="17d11f6f-c883-4f86-9287-9ecc85742a0c">
      <Text>She looks at Kevin. Dead to the world. Looks back at the phone. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="b54d69d1-be5c-4016-b0ed-660b25cb570d">
      <Text>Types: "Always." </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="e130ff34-aeb9-4d69-a730-b735b60877a9">
      <Text>Three dots appear. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="fc2f4292-d2f4-4584-931a-b1ff329420dd">
      <Text>Then: C.M.: "Thinking about the boat already." </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="e6514829-1978-43a8-bf19-e2853fe4983c">
      <Text>Janet's thumb hovers over the keyboard. A small smile—the first real one we've seen from her tonight. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="a6f5d5d0-7a19-4500-a51a-b7c9db1909c9">
      <Text>She types: "New bikini, huh?. I’ll make sure you'll approve." </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="333d6444-e941-431e-b663-dfefefce1ceb">
      <Text>She pulls up another text chat, a contact ironically still saved as Doorman Bill.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="82238efc-25dc-4d56-a218-a0358aa9cb89">
      <Text>Types: You’re still here? I could use another hand with the... groceries. 5 minutes in the foyer.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d5dc8fc6-8ce9-4824-93ab-18b6bc60b386">
      <Text>Walks to her side of the bed—the far side.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="3f7b88bb-e4ca-404d-8134-d142910648e3">
      <Text>JANET</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="ddd8998e-bff3-4a49-9894-0d188bc17048">
      <Text>(barely audible)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="e626c5ef-8d7c-47bd-a31f-8dbe445ea7b9">
      <Text>Goodnight, Kevin.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="2ef64b5b-7e88-4924-b0a8-4f5210e3c12b">
      <Text>He doesn't stir. She turns away from him. Doesn’t bother with a cover up. Heads for the door.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="3558eb74-4689-4308-9e45-abfe32d1da6a">
      <SceneProperties Length="2 6/8" Page="18" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="JAMIE">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="JAZ">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. JAZ'S BEDROOM - NIGHT</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="b31dd50d-6a9a-46b3-9488-0480e5e197c7">
      <Text>The door is locked and chained. The textbook is on the desk, unopened.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="1ba29c3c-fdc8-4cd7-af52-04160c0b299f">
      <Text>JAZ stands at her closet, still in the Princeton sweatshirt, the ponytail, the good-daughter costume. She pulls a canvas messenger bag from behind a row of clothes her mother picked out and she's never worn.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="5f850202-76c3-45db-bab0-95cea9ca988b">
      <Text>From a hidden compartment in the back of the closet, she retrieves items and stuffs them into the bag with practiced efficiency.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="b037a8fc-0007-4404-80f3-1ed361c4f95f">
      <Text>She zips the bag. Checks herself in the mirror—still the admissions brochure. Perfect.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="6799050a-15a9-4045-9310-e60e14ebed76">
      <Text>She picks up her phone. Types a quick message.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="a346c814-db58-4582-9799-feff4368ce83">
      <Text>JAZ (TEXT)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="a8cea2a7-f177-4299-9581-732cec99962e">
      <Text>got a sec?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="b2398721-818a-4138-ba71-573612ef24a4">
      <Text>THREE SECONDS LATER—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d32c7b6b-e642-43ff-a571-23ec4ed96af8">
      <Text>A soft knock at the balcony door. The French doors that connect to a shared balcony between her room and Jamie's.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="94fde52f-6edd-4bd3-b4b1-5139c81a0aa8">
      <Text>She opens it.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="bddb90a8-6f30-496c-aabd-5edebacbd757">
      <Text>JAMIE stands there, bathed in the blue glow spilling over from his room of whatever screens he was just staring at. Hoodie and joggers. Looking exactly like what their parents think he is.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="76c59924-25f8-42e9-92c3-ca66c2645b5d">
      <Text>He clocks the bag. Doesn't blink.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="0f36da28-6090-464e-b083-ddc808897bd5">
      <Text>JAMIE</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="05628071-0bd4-4458-a923-71ad154cf691">
      <Text>So much for the midterms, I guess.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="81c6b9f2-8869-4ce3-84da-ad2674d96a21">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="9fa1d263-2c07-4984-8895-9c715162c516">
      <Text>(checking her phone)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="e9548609-89b0-46e4-913a-0c35d8b7b1fe">
      <Text>I don't even know why you bother going to that school. I can just tell the dean to mark you there. I have him handled.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="28f39bb4-d679-4dff-9d7f-fa38a6e3e765">
      <Text>JAMIE</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="2b1e193c-b575-498d-ac88-9b62f916716f">
      <Text>I like the library. It's quiet. And there's a girl in my physics class who does this thing with her pencil when she's thinking—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="ab3aaee8-4ae6-4a34-b628-c06a595a3bf3">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="d3985d83-229c-4228-92d4-4f87f399930a">
      <Text>(holding up a hand)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="f5e6335e-be50-475f-9084-d37902f962a2">
      <Text>Stopping you there. Don't need to know about your pencil fetish.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="f9d725ea-d2d0-46a1-a361-918beeadfee0">
      <Text>JAMIE</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="518562d6-60bf-4fcb-8b76-442f6afa268c">
      <Text>It's not a fetish. It's an observation.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="a3db0faf-d885-49e9-a03e-1664f2da9e4e">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="e6c8e1b1-3650-4e57-92b8-1b63f38cbab5">
      <Text>Sure it is.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="a2affbfb-3da7-4a72-93c1-fe7e7cb596ac">
      <Text>She doesn't push it. Everyone in this family has their reasons for leaving this house.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="2ec055bd-af30-4f5e-b1fe-4573d3b7c4fa">
      <Text>JAMIE</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="6795a596-9c56-48bb-8611-259fc11591d9">
      <Text>Where tonight?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="189ebba8-31b2-419e-ae88-8399e6f8b4d7">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="22c1257b-9356-40e7-b242-9fa28d688210">
      <Text>Declan's band is playing some abandoned station under Delancey tonight. The one with the rats.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="75a4213a-0cc2-4a90-aa36-dda82dfb9f1c">
      <Text>JAMIE</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="74b56479-3045-42cb-a986-727c9c753861">
      <Text>Which one with the rats.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="99b6442a-da80-4c61-a448-554e8e008572">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="93430d38-8a0a-43ad-9b14-7e2b35e0ef57">
      <Text>(small smile)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="2c168626-0163-4369-9c9f-efcc3fbf771d">
      <Text>Fair. After that, I promised the degenerates in Chinatown I'd let them try to win back some of the cash I took off them last game.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="c8507bd0-cf9f-4729-8352-cbe06caa900d">
      <Text>JAMIE</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="26d62a46-e704-4d37-af2a-a2073a562f43">
      <Text>The triad-adjacent guys?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="4459a654-8a0b-43e7-8342-737c544d69dc">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="6fd18e3e-e527-4f10-a7f9-8a312b657560">
      <Text>(laughing)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="501cf961-9336-4a46-9471-a3199d4c1c35">
      <Text>They fucking wish... more like crazy rich traders with a Yakuza fetish. All of them are just losing family money and calling it trading.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="7fb6a20f-3c70-4ce6-916f-b651ad82ede2">
      <Text>JAMIE</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="99637721-cb9e-4bb1-8feb-16e428c17f0f">
      <Text>You took twelve thousand off them.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="9b9aa62f-59f8-4389-b9a0-63b6e0c038b6">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="889f1a9b-7c56-4f4c-a141-179491feaf4c">
      <Text>And they're very motivated to get it back. Which means the pot will be fat.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="8f1fbb92-37ef-4351-b9ca-cf101f046c0b">
      <Text>(turning to him)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="32f58b40-b430-4635-b127-4d254867ea6c">
      <Text>Speaking of which—you got my buy-in?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="c250807a-e2ec-48cd-a64b-26b686875fc7">
      <Text>Jamie reaches into his hoodie pocket and produces a banded stack of bills. Ten thousand dollars. Neat. Crisp.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="5c2728af-24b9-4fe1-8b53-74d12d9e7ec1">
      <Text>He tosses it to her.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="024ec00b-03ab-451f-ae87-673c662dbc1f">
      <Text>She catches it one-handed, rifles through it with a practiced thumb, tucks it into a zippered pocket inside the messenger bag.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="a4723535-5259-4273-b456-f0ee8b62617f">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="29c9624f-8a2a-4961-b3ef-8f17d6f58185">
      <Text>You're the best banker a girl could ask for.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="20d03c67-e3cb-4818-9cfa-dc59f08e13c3">
      <Text>She crosses to him, takes his face in her hands, and plants a kiss on his forehead. Genuine. Warm. The most real thing that's happened in this house all night.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="399259b7-1b96-4642-9fee-c219850c441a">
      <Text>JAMIE</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="9a4f7dd8-abff-47be-8f01-61298cf8665e">
      <Text>Don't get stabbed.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="788dc7d2-0276-437b-b784-7bd04f44b2dd">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="1e3f692f-a6db-4fa2-98eb-837169bd4bf2">
      <Text>That was one time. And it was more of a graze. Ok, twice...</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="dd083993-cb50-4de7-83d1-1f7d810f814e">
      <Text>She slings the bag over her shoulder— and slips out the balcony door.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="702d8a60-6fa7-4c63-afa0-3f3a9badb6cf">
      <Text>Jamie watches her scale down the trellis like a panther and disappear over the garden wall into the dark.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="0d195149-1d3e-4e71-bc3f-b105e2736a3e">
      <Text>He stands there a moment. Then pulls out his phone—a GPS tracker app, a small blinking dot landing just in front of the house.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="97870713-1cdb-4836-b5f3-e2ddfb4bf643">
      <Text>JAMIE</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="eab278dd-e5b1-4b6c-915a-9040589f7e31">
      <Text>(to himself)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="fce8d8a4-93aa-40fe-846b-fa0177601e13">
      <Text>Just in case.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d0f92a28-0f49-42d1-b410-8629e2aa52d8">
      <Text>He heads back to his room.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="b68f67d7-f17c-4987-a6f6-8fb31f3d15ad">
      <SceneProperties Length="1" Page="21" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="JAMIE">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. JAMIE'S BEDROOM - CONTINUOUS</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="ae7cfe56-af57-4248-b376-cc8f9ff3bc19">
      <Text>Six monitors. Three keyboards. The hum of cooling fans flush liquid cooled radiators. A setup that would make a hedge fund quant jealous—or nervous.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d9527eb6-1112-46ec-a16a-b10e67b6adde">
      <Text>Jamie settles into his chair. Pulls up another window.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="8a187e6a-7e0e-41e6-81cd-b94987e825d9">
      <Text>A file directory labeled "DAD_CO / MERKUR_ACQUISITION"</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="bc11f376-041b-4adf-879b-e09984746cb9">
      <Text>He's been here before. Many times. His father's corporate servers have had a quiet passenger for years.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="e596f78e-2ac0-463c-a8c9-9256c4abe0b1">
      <Text>Jamie scrolls through financials. Cap tables. Internal memos. The stuff Kevin thinks is locked behind enterprise-grade encryption.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="7272b536-6410-45aa-b64b-564a3deac9c5">
      <Text>He opens a spreadsheet. Cross-references it against another. Frowns.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="44d7ddb4-984f-4de3-8b27-13a6d3470093">
      <Text>Opens a third document. Bank routing numbers. Wire transfers.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="27c17e00-66cd-46f3-be2d-48ab7ecb5753">
      <Text>His fingers stop.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="cd1b43bc-118f-4928-8ae9-a2da627b3541">
      <Text>JAMIE</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="cec1eaf4-3cfa-4b48-b52f-67c791f789ea">
      <Text>(quietly)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="a20a9897-49e6-4e75-ac50-22ef2910b812">
      <Text>That's not right.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="dcdd2def-b4f9-4eed-bef3-11e6806fbb8b">
      <Text>He pulls up a calculator. Runs numbers. Checks them again.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="f1e66642-8368-4678-aef6-20eaa4be352f">
      <Text>On screen, we see what he sees—columns that don't add up. Transfers to accounts that don't match any vendor or partner. A pattern.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="bf0744ea-6392-459f-a31c-47ba0ad23b54">
      <Text>JAMIE</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="bcb18d20-96cd-40dc-adc3-d71a52fd5bd5">
      <Text>(to himself)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="b2a02420-85ff-4f7f-873c-c3d8bf8ef39f">
      <Text>Thirty-two million... forty-seven... sixty...</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="a79d6c77-4156-402c-b4f0-9b92518cfba1">
      <Text>He opens another file. Board compensation records. Stock option exercises. A trail of breadcrumbs leading somewhere his father definitely doesn't know about.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="25234f4a-14f2-43bb-bd29-7bf802761996">
      <Text>Or maybe does.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="27ece451-b11d-4444-bbfe-e6c30345fae1">
      <Text>Jamie leans back. Stares at the screen.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="0062289c-fecf-46c6-a044-17cc5935e53f">
      <Text>JAMIE</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="e71313ee-fbc5-4162-9327-f4e320da92f0">
      <Text>Shit.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="fd9cfb65-c164-47fe-a439-a18fedbbd792">
      <SceneProperties Length="3" Page="22" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="JAZ">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>EXT. MCCORT TOWNHOUSE - STREET LEVEL - NIGHT</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="e927ad80-5013-4ebf-8dca-7dff1a5f245e">
      <Text>JAZ drops the last few feet from the garden wall, landing soft on the sidewalk.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="ae87fb8e-ddb7-42d7-aacc-83d5c7774f23">
      <Text>She adjusts the messenger bag on her shoulder and moves toward the front of the townhouse— </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="f0f2f34b-f3a9-417e-b2c1-9456f6c7daa0">
      <Text>And stops. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="05570424-4ceb-40f4-b87b-c18d2825a911">
      <Text>Through the foyer window— frosted glass, but not frosted enough— she can see shapes. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="c7320d0a-4aaf-4839-9e3a-882a331d5193">
      <Text>Movement. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="35211ad4-df80-4634-9d22-e44c52f5c03e">
      <Text>And she can hear it now: the unmistakable rhythm of two people who are very much not discussing groceries. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="44dc81e8-2d39-412a-82a3-5ffc3a1f34eb">
      <Text>Through the glass JANET is bent over the reclaimed-wood console table— the one with the $400 lilies— and BILL THE DOORMAN is behind her, uniform pants around his ankles, going at it like he's trying to make up for every minute he spent saying "Good evening, Mr. McCort." </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="55b36e95-b7ad-4b67-8057-b337d8c8d8bc">
      <Text>The lilies are taking a beating. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="318afb48-e49a-4433-8641-aa11ea9ba1e9">
      <Text>Jaz watches for a moment. Her expression isn't shock. Isn't disgust. It's... The tired amusement of someone who's seen this movie many, many times.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="c41433e7-b68d-4626-8ea9-827e9c162925">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="885e98c5-1e21-4204-86a3-c56759f90b39">
      <Text>(under her breath, genuine admiration)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="7356c364-ef6d-404f-9f72-eed584174314">
      <Text>Get it, Mom.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="2de4d439-8940-40f7-88b4-5ee686395a60">
      <Text>She settles just out of the light spilling from the window, and gets to work. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="e510a777-a003-4bd3-a184-0e674816f6ff">
      <Text>First: the Princeton sweatshirt. She peels it over her head, revealing what's underneath— </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="e44660a4-6104-49db-8785-60b20d1fdb0f">
      <Text>The world's smallest black bralette, barely more than a suggestion of fabric, framed by a severe black leather harness. Straps crisscross her torso, silver O-rings glinting, the whole apparatus extending down beneath her sweatpants. This wasn't put on as an afterthought. This is her cherished second skin. The real outfit. Everything else was costume.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="8751863f-7929-40fb-9377-3c4075bbec7b">
      <Text>Sweatshirt into the bag. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="1abc8539-ac03-4cfc-bc32-a8ad4a02893a">
      <Text>From inside the foyer, a muffled moan. Bill's doing something right, apparently. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="3e160de5-7470-47d8-a007-d0ebe824f968">
      <Text>Jaz smirks. Keeps going. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="933f31bc-ff0a-4ec3-b55c-78732548aed2">
      <Text>The sweatpants come next. She whips them down and steps out— revealing the shortest shorts imaginable, rainbow-striped, torn at the edges, sitting above shredded fishnet stockings that have seen genuine combat. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="0d604d63-30e4-461c-8195-9bafc74094a6">
      <Text>Into the bag. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="48752b68-f07b-42d9-b6ff-f40a511c92e1">
      <Text>She pulls out the combat boots. Black leather, steel-toed, covered in band ink and what might be old blood. Is definitely blood.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="b0e606d1-ca21-4ecb-92e3-5f7268bb14b2">
      <Text>She plops down on the steps and begins lacing them up with practiced speed. Tapping her foot to the rhythm that is banging out the beats from inside the glass.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="626d7053-6f9c-42ac-9fbd-e1462d878bf7">
      <Text>A glance back at the window. Janet's hands are splayed on the table now. The lilies are definitely done for.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="7d3a48b8-6db0-44f9-8362-2d28a6c46de1">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="d00fd867-4c48-4be9-b607-2fe9a3360b35">
      <Text>(lacing, conversational)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="765474f0-9386-4b01-a1ad-c57315665b9e">
      <Text>Eleven minutes. Pretty good Bill, got that cardio.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d0c11409-4856-4956-9ec1-4e46da2bc034">
      <Text>Boots: done. She stands. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="9dbfa784-6005-4c05-b31a-6804db2de1c2">
      <Text>Next: the hair. She can’t shed that shit fast enough.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="8133e2e9-1fca-46aa-a843-2bc0910cbd8d">
      <Text>She reaches up and pulls— the extensions come out in one practiced motion, the clips releasing, the glossy chestnut curtain gone. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d5a07dbd-a49d-4e64-8dea-b58c758a7c2f">
      <Text>Underneath: chaos. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="63ba876e-a82f-48e0-a1d3-545a89a2d9df">
      <Text>One side of her head shaved close, revealing a tattoo that crawls from behind her ear down toward her neck—an intricate pattern of thorns and flowers and what might be a snake eating itself. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="59796c07-9fa5-4b2a-b317-5dae71e50a36">
      <Text>The other side is long, razor-cut, dyed black with streaks of electric blue that catch the streetlight. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="79ea2e66-a09a-4737-8566-530813016915">
      <Text>She shoves the extensions into the bag. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="9083654e-6abb-4ac2-bfee-b867186d9d17">
      <Text>Another glance at the window. Still going. Mom's got stamina. Or Bill does. Or both.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="8fe78ae5-5487-461e-b0d2-d54cfe5209b2">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="e537441f-1679-4604-ace0-ee9d580dfdfc">
      <Text>(genuine)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="17f6724b-a269-4ac4-837e-4c09739d6438">
      <Text>Respect.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="3217a766-98a8-44cc-90df-7e608ee88975">
      <Text>She moves to the side of the stoop, where the package delivery bin sits—a locked metal box for Amazon drops and the like. She knows the code. She punches it in. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="6d1550b5-167e-4a99-9add-42b99f236e34">
      <Text>Inside, hidden beneath a decoy package labeled "ORGANIC DOG TREATS" </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="7b390740-c511-4d88-95f1-234d86848991">
      <Text>The leather. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="fe8661ab-f9b8-4173-854d-bba2b741a677">
      <Text>She pulls it out. It's magnificent in its destruction—black leather, ancient, covered in patches and safety pins. Anarchy symbols. Band logos. A hand-stitched patch that reads "THE FUTURE IS FEMALE AND SHE IS HER OWN." Studs along the collar. A faded Misfits skull on the back. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="a191bfbc-fc72-46b6-bde6-108ed7ac7929">
      <Text>She shrugs it on. Home. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="2c1f2cf5-b115-476b-958e-af8246bc256b">
      <Text>One final touch. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="b72324f3-2dfc-4591-be95-26e17df92375">
      <Text>She reaches up to her nose—and from somewhere deep inside her nostrils, hidden all through family dinner and good-daughter performance, she flips down a septum ring. Silver. Brutal. The kind of thing that would give Kevin a stroke. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="a5a4ed86-b9e9-453d-9a77-27b474d2182f">
      <Text>She looks at her reflection in a parked car's window. The transformation is complete. Tank Girl incarnate.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="a8b6a2c8-3b0c-412c-a530-d9c48d8397c5">
      <Text>This is Jaz. The real one. She looks like she might start a riot... or star in one. Or Both.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="5cb0a30b-b036-4a72-85f0-0de4fe652b30">
      <Text>Her deep blue eyes burn with life.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="28ecfd88-45ae-4196-b7f0-36e4aa13fa88">
      <Text>She takes one last look at the foyer window. Bill appears to be finishing. Janet's head is thrown back.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="4ccc7127-3cde-49f7-9094-02494b18c4aa">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="a11c5bbe-2d28-40f7-bdf2-c997bf4b605d">
      <Text>(saluting the window)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="4327c215-94bb-46a2-9082-dc1f24e3dacf">
      <Text>Same time next week, Bill.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="65452f71-cf3e-4e27-89a8-563ebcb374ee">
      <Text>She turns and walks down West 84th Street, combat boots striking pavement, harness glinting under streetlights, heading toward the subway and whatever beautiful disaster is waiting for her underground. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="70803335-443b-4602-9d91-c0a35d00c5f9">
      <Text>Full flair. Full freedom. Fully herself. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="844a8060-e54d-49ec-935f-be90545989c5">
      <Text>HOLD on her figure receding into the New York night—a live creature emerging from a cocoon of cashmere and lies.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="b863180c-bc37-4cac-a936-ac1be4240929">
      <Text>Behind her, the townhouse glows. Perfect and silent and full of secrets.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="3f855681-e023-4831-9f1d-62b873a53728">
      <SceneProperties Length="6/8" Page="25" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. MCCORT TOWNHOUSE - MASTER SUITE - LATER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="24f28a49-1197-40b4-b46f-18f6a06fcd0d">
      <Text>The room is dark. The 85-inch Samsung is off. The only light: a thin blade of moon through the automated shades.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="045ea6ab-d9bc-46c9-ace2-1bdd3e218e31">
      <Text>KEVIN is exactly where we left him—except now he's rolled onto his side, still in his dress shirt, mouth slightly open, the Patek catching moonlight on his wrist. The sleep of the conqueror.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="eb7aba25-4eda-456f-81fe-057f37d6a308">
      <Text>The door opens. Quietly.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="856068bd-3190-4e18-9ea9-e0f11125bd93">
      <Text>JANET slips in.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d71aa74c-8594-469b-8869-f7dd2ca513c0">
      <Text>The $2,000 La Perla negligee is... different now. Twisted. One strap hanging off her shoulder. The silk wrinkled in ways silk isn't supposed to wrinkle.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="a9a56030-2a13-4f5b-af6b-3e6cbd3e5355">
      <Text>And her face.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="2d0d2fe1-d9c2-450c-9bee-60eb250a546c">
      <Text>The makeup that was immaculate two hours ago is now a crime scene. Mascara smudged beneath her eyes. Lipstick smeared past the borders of her lips, trailing toward her chin. Foundation disturbed by sweat, by friction, by a hand gripping her jaw at some point.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="e757eb9d-c7ec-426d-a413-56841f290ab2">
      <Text>She looks like a beautiful painting left out in the rain.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="9afe6fbc-2cca-4db7-a440-ecef23d189d6">
      <Text>She stands at the foot of the bed. Watches her husband sleep.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="ab3a705d-eaa2-46bd-b9e5-22d57b972faa">
      <Text>He doesn't stir. Doesn't sense her. Doesn't know.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="bcf20b21-98a7-46fe-aedf-7f064a0306d2">
      <Text>Has never known.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="cde5d8aa-0717-4302-9a3d-05e448489f01">
      <Text>Janet's expression isn't guilt. Isn't shame. It's something closer to exhaustion. The tiredness of maintaining two complete lives in the same body.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="3f9f887a-365e-48c7-931e-1a8d3fc8a588">
      <Text>She turns and pads toward the ensuite bathroom.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="3b3a7040-65e0-45d7-a41b-69a268458846">
      <SceneProperties Length="7/8" Page="26" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. MASTER ENSUITE - CONTINUOUS</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="247e02e1-7874-460e-8764-4a6e8063b9b7">
      <Text>White marble. Heated floors. A shower with seventeen heads and a control panel like a spaceship.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="74fce1b3-35ec-452f-88b9-3aefb61bdfd7">
      <Text>Janet closes the door softly. Catches herself in the mirror.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="bf49cb7e-c81d-4300-b5d7-a0d2c49ce9e2">
      <Text>She looks at her reflection for a long moment. Studies the wreckage. Doesn't flinch.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="3d671787-e0b1-4b38-90e5-40173e778827">
      <Text>Then—efficient, practiced—she peels off the negligee. It pools on the floor, expensive and ruined.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="43c0f456-dcc0-4f86-ae84-b997e65ca4ed">
      <Text>Her underwear follows. The delicate La Perla thong—soaked, translucent, unmistakably used—arcs through the air and lands in the hamper with a wet whisper.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="5bbafc59-bdee-40e0-9f72-cc4355b57740">
      <Text>Tomorrow Maria will do the laundry without comment. She always does. The hazard pay is built into her salary.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="ee432dda-debe-49ff-bec1-e68589b06582">
      <Text>Janet turns on the shower. All seventeen heads. Steam begins to fill the room.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="8a60cd6f-d6a1-4993-b27a-c624e1c1c4f7">
      <Text>She steps in.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="657df1df-9c5e-492f-8e27-b47b04eeb9df">
      <Text>The water hits her- hot, punishing- and she tilts her face up into it. Eyes closed. Letting it wash away Bill, and the foyer, and the lilies she'll have to replace, and the text from Chet she hasn't answered yet, and the husband who looked right through her tonight, and all the other men who haven't.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="391d152b-d445-434d-96f4-22922b0f179a">
      <Text>Her hands move mechanically. Soap. Rinse. Erase.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="8a624da7-52b2-4b41-a381-eace4e286725">
      <Text>This is not her first time performing this ritual. It will not be her last.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="dccb3656-2a20-48db-9951-40749f3dadc3">
      <Text>HOLD on her silhouette through the fogged glass. A woman disappearing into steam. Cleaning the evidence. Resetting for tomorrow.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="9bdd7fe5-a1cb-4044-98a1-81c55bd65f6e">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="26" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>EXT. LOWER EAST SIDE - DELANCEY STREET - NIGHT</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="74dbafad-de1e-4b0b-9bd3-3086d6850470">
      <Text>A block that gentrification forgot. Or gave up on. Shuttered storefronts. A check-cashing place with bulletproof glass. The distant rumble of the J train overhead. JAZ walks with purpose, combat boots eating pavement, the leather jacket a second skin. She turns down an alley that doesn't appear on Google Maps.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="fda8897d-a5ef-4df9-b2e3-51870c621845">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 1/8" Page="27" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="JAZ">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="RATCHET">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="SPIKE">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>EXT. ALLEY - CONTINUOUS</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="5bf9d342-cffb-44ee-b3eb-d8d6fd98d411">
      <Text>Dumpsters. Fire escapes. The smell of piss and something burning. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="1ae618a5-3f0b-4e89-9e84-d401eb48dfc1">
      <Text>At the end of the alley: a chain-link fence with a hole cut in it, and beyond that, a rusted door set into concrete. The old service entrance to an abandoned subway station. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="8ee2865e-f771-42a1-83d2-e4798b5de2a1">
      <Text>Two figures materialize from the shadows. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="c7422c9e-e678-457b-ba9a-7c3e9c317049">
      <Text>SPIKE (20s) is six-foot-four with a green mohawk that adds another eight inches. Face tattoos. Nose ring connected by chain to his ear. Arms like he's been lifting dumpsters for sport. He looks like he'd kill you for a cigarette. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="84c2a252-8d58-44e0-a8f2-7dd36b417c6d">
      <Text>RATCHET (30s, non-binary) is smaller, wiry, head shaved clean except for a single long braid dyed white. They're wearing what appears to be a straitjacket repurposed as a vest. A walkie-talkie crackles on their hip. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="5c7676c9-c92a-4780-b141-9379bc2d6aa4">
      <Text>They block the path.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="e2ebfebe-e465-4198-aa82-221daad28178">
      <Text>SPIKE</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="0e516c42-f8b2-4ddb-b242-ae2bed8a934b">
      <Text>(dead voice)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="900513fd-24dc-4cfc-9b90-3e0d7ffeda06">
      <Text>The fuck you want.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="289cfef8-7dbe-4883-bac6-d899a147ec34">
      <Text>A beat. Then his face breaks into a massive grin.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="b6468e65-12c4-4338-9645-07d14f6b7435">
      <Text>SPIKE</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="ba305bff-7baf-4fb7-a748-4d12cb7453c4">
      <Text>Jazzy! You beautiful disaster!</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d89b81c9-9f55-4751-9259-40a6cb3cab9e">
      <Text>He scoops her into a bear hug that lifts her off the ground.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="3cfdac77-8844-4b14-9661-5c3aede00d04">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="eb60d030-12b1-4f08-ae4b-bf53e45c8a33">
      <Text>(muffled against his chest)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="ca1ee9dc-929d-4575-b071-55f63f2236da">
      <Text>Spike. Ribs. Ribs.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="f594ffc1-ddfb-4dec-83de-a2e796806c64">
      <Text>SPIKE</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="b7dfc47e-b716-4289-ad79-73f19a67ac21">
      <Text>(setting her down)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="996e2ae9-d468-4ff5-8acc-4631f34f26e6">
      <Text>Sorry. I just get excited. You declined the Discord invite.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="d667c57e-1218-4d4b-9d71-20614d1080a3">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="de0e4940-0876-4480-9e54-9c9dfda40dae">
      <Text>I lied. I do that.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="102a9f88-a004-487a-b08e-5a0001b4c35f">
      <Text>RATCHET</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="da46cf09-492a-4294-8965-52c4eb8f8d0b">
      <Text>(already on walkie)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="3768f9a3-2506-464d-813a-3794f1f0a4cb">
      <Text>Phoenix is here. Yeah. The Phoenix.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="eebc4753-e44f-4db4-b95a-7ae2e36165e7">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="de0e019c-4873-488a-b0bb-51a88d081288">
      <Text>You're plus-zero tonight?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="cad16a50-3312-4606-b367-bb5bf43d76ac">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="a2bec186-6cf6-44e6-b563-666582df2d4f">
      <Text>you know me, my love, no baggage- Chinatown after.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="5ba5a4ef-70ac-46e3-8760-ea6a1e94c0f5">
      <Text>Spike pulls open the rusted door. It swings smooth and silent—recently oiled, despite appearances.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="087ac075-2db8-4553-86aa-d9e9dadddac7">
      <SceneProperties Length="3/8" Page="28" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. ABANDONED SUBWAY TUNNEL - NIGHT</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="41be116d-b743-422a-8f8e-54316efc23ad">
      <Text>A narrow passage. Concrete walls slick with condensation. Pipes overhead, some dripping, some wrapped in Christmas lights that flicker like dying stars.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="45e29683-e662-4567-b547-7a9afa7513fa">
      <Text>JAZ moves fast. Almost running. The SOUND is ahead of her- muffled at first, then louder with every step, a heartbeat getting closer, a beast waking up.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="6099b44d-7566-456b-9fab-09c5cf8db6f6">
      <Text>She can feel it in her chest now. The bass. The drums. The ROAR of something alive.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="2e3f7a81-fec8-47c9-b9b3-ab7d502e1e30">
      <Text>The tunnel curves. The lights get sparser. The sound gets LOUDER.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="8ff978de-7bfd-4eaf-a361-1951695d7923">
      <Text>She's smiling. That real smile. Running toward the thing that makes her real.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="ce283de1-45fd-4001-a6a7-0ce40aa13ba1">
      <SceneProperties Length="3" Page="28" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="JAZ &amp; DECLAN">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. ABANDONED SUBWAY STATION - CONTINUOUS</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="bdcff252-24ec-46aa-b4e7-ef0339334ce9">
      <Text>The tunnel opens—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="233e373e-093d-4101-b1d8-6a46e403d3e2">
      <Text>And there it is.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="3901747d-9d96-4f09-a880-050bf79761ea">
      <Text>A cathedral of sweat and noise.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="8a889ab9-7c1b-4c55-89e3-36768d27aa1a">
      <Text>The vaulted tile ceiling soars overhead, cracked and graffitied, original 1920s bones left to rot and reborn as something holier. Somewhere down there, a makeshift stage. Somewhere down there, lights slashing through smoke and steam rising off bodies.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="768bb520-adbe-45b4-84e9-a5bd087c62da">
      <Text>But what Jaz sees from up here on the old maintenance catwalk is the PIT.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="0a581763-4dc8-4a3b-8159-8875e229c52a">
      <Text>Three hundred bodies. Maybe more. GRINDING. A single organism made of leather and skin and fury, PULSING to music that's less song than assault. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="39534177-551b-4ffc-9ecc-c5801b9ed66a">
      <Text>The crowd doesn't dance—it CHURNS, a sea with its own tides, people appearing and disappearing, elbows and fists and mouths open screaming lyrics or just screaming.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="fce80fa2-3cae-4f71-80d8-c7f69d462603">
      <Text>It's violent. It's beautiful. It's hers.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="8442ce13-b28c-47f8-9965-eece4f9f4b17">
      <Text>Jaz grips the rusted railing. Looks down. Twenty feet, maybe. Enough to break something if the crowd wasn't there.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="f7542990-ac98-425f-88c0-f3bfaefc99ae">
      <Text>The crowd is there.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="c13d4b2b-b046-4c83-87c6-7319cf12356e">
      <Text>She doesn't hesitate.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="6378a878-b573-43a4-b853-79d5e69ef214">
      <Text>She RUNS—three steps along the catwalk—and LAUNCHES herself over the banister.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Transition" id="bf9c2629-26b4-418a-9808-ad2b3da19411">
      <Text>SLOW MOTION:</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="4d9c9cbd-bbb8-49d1-b957-46b73494aa6e">
      <Text>Jaz in the air. Arms wide. Jacket flaring. Face split in a grin that's half joy, half madness. Falling toward the chaos like she's coming home.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Transition" id="70f6b46d-da0d-4beb-a42c-2a74a1f5279f">
      <Text>REAL TIME:</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="bfb27b3b-35d3-4030-b233-83331dbf27a5">
      <Text>She HITS the crowd—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="70a2ffa7-3aa6-484a-adbd-affcabc6ff74">
      <Text>And the crowd CATCHES her.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="e34a12fc-fd73-4f24-b70c-8ef860f7e7b5">
      <Text>A hundred hands. Strangers' hands. They're everywhere instantly- on her back, her legs, her arms, her ass, her ribs. She's horizontal now, floating, SURFING on a sea of fingers and palms.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="ba1e6961-b473-4b18-8a96-3bfe5c59a731">
      <Text>The current takes her.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="4833e364-398a-4e1a-aca7-ddd59e91598b">
      <Text>She has no control. Doesn't want any. Hands move her— groping, pulling, pushing. Someone yanks her hair and she LAUGHS. Fingers find the straps of her harness, lace through the O-rings, and those grips become the prevailing tide, dragging her forward, toward the stage.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="915d707d-46c1-4913-9662-305bf1ec012e">
      <Text>The bralette doesn't survive. Her hands catch it, pull, and it's GONE—torn away, swallowed by the pit, a sacrifice to the chaos gods. She doesn't care. Can't care. One less thing between her and the noise.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="11ed9646-5898-4829-9266-8baf90f66e3d">
      <Text>She floats on her back, prone like the crucifix, staring up at the cracked cathedral ceiling strobing with light, bodies beneath her shifting and surging, and she is LOST in it. Her happy place. Anonymous and known. Touched by everyone, owned by no one. Completely free and accepted.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="ccbfc5cb-6c22-40ae-b9df-6999c3deb10e">
      <Text>The current keeps pulling.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="94c11f5e-d965-4901-94ff-7b36acc4e4c2">
      <Text>On stage: DECLAN.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="4cc128ab-af5a-4492-a5a8-3cb7c6b4696b">
      <Text>He's in a studded leather G-string and nothing else. His body is a roadmap of tattoos, drenched in sweat, muscles cording as he SCREAMS into a mic held like a weapon. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="3162ca62-dcbd-4b45-b5ed-03fceebf7b4c">
      <Text>Liberty spikes—green, six inches—jut from his skull like a crown.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d917e74c-52bb-436d-837b-da92559b7e44">
      <Text>Behind him, the band HAMMERS—shirtless drummer, bassist with a shaved head and blood trickling from her nose (mosh pit casualty, still playing), guitarist thrashing like he's trying to murder his instrument.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="533e281b-75f2-4a33-8c32-55e179158d3a">
      <Text>The sound is DEAFENING. Beyond music. A wall of fury you feel in your teeth.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="57835c45-6ced-4517-8a34-b0777265f5d0">
      <Text>Jaz floats closer. Hands keep passing her forward, person to person, grip to grip. Her remaining clothes are wrecked—one shoulder strap of the destroyed bralette still dangles uselessly, one boot completely unlaced and threatening to come off.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d3946b94-0f15-405e-8095-f2dbe6423af0">
      <Text>She doesn't care. She's almost there.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="86638a19-c5ec-4cf4-a269-5e6c66835d4d">
      <Text>The crowd SURGES—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="b888bf29-b77a-4c3d-89ab-e406ee0ac4fa">
      <Text>And she's EJECTED onto the stage.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="01afa392-0fcf-407a-adc7-5d6073aff92b">
      <Text>Boots hit wood. She stumbles, catches herself, and she's UP—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="7229ca2a-2ee9-4c7a-8b00-f035fa46e9f1">
      <Text>Standing in the lights. In the noise. In the heat radiating off Declan's body as he stomps toward her mid-lyric, sweat flying off him like rain.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="739046e1-0b91-4b05-9da3-ee55d7ac80bc">
      <Text>She's a beautiful disaster. Topless, harness askew, hair wild, one boot flopping, grinning like a demon.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="409a8782-d9f8-4f88-8f1e-12f9f97a02ae">
      <Text>She grabs Declan by a liberty spike—just GRABS it, yanks his face to hers— and KISSES him. Deep. Violent. His free hand finds her waist, pulls her in, the mic between them catching the wet sound of it.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="6cadef7b-8e52-446f-b263-a1db8b468997">
      <Text>She BREAKS the kiss—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="54edcca3-860c-4b85-9644-9cad78d9c245">
      <Text>Both of them turn to the mic—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="9919a92e-3ce5-415f-8e61-a3c8bc8f5ed3">
      <Text>And SCREAM the chorus together:</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="b1feb090-0add-4794-a9e5-b2ea99c90dc6">
      <Text>JAZ &amp; DECLAN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="73e20921-6f1d-4d53-86c9-8447f06271a4">
      <Text>(in unison, into the mic)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="7d81210b-229c-4335-adc8-b9b0cc9f1513">
      <Text>NOW I WANNA BE YOUR DOG—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="203e91c9-8b12-4626-ba20-9a7797bd3413">
      <Text>The crowd ERUPTS. A wave of sound that hits like a physical force. The pit SWELLS, bodies crashing against the stage, hands reaching up like supplicants.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="1bad64cd-8a5d-4a88-acc6-284553385288">
      <Text>Another body comes flying—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="875276b8-edfa-44a1-8c34-f1d861e4ea60">
      <Text>EJECTED from the crowd onto the stage beside them. An entirely androgynous human—shaved head, smeared eyeliner, shirtless, covered in glitter and someone else's blood, chest heaving, grinning wild.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="97b0f4fa-7847-41ed-b54e-237ecde09c2b">
      <Text>Jaz GRABS them. Spins them in a twirl like they're at a debutante ball in hell. Their bodies collide—sweaty, sticky, alive—and she KISSES them too. Just as deep. Just as real.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="364d8b63-cda5-4172-96a1-816925f1787f">
      <Text>The stranger kisses back like their life depends on it.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="be189225-a466-41bd-94cf-c9c38c914e65">
      <Text>Jaz breaks it. Locks eyes. Grins.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="e7abb8e7-1242-4e4d-a483-c5a793a6c17c">
      <Text>Then she shoves them gently backward- and LAUNCHES herself off the stage, back into the pit.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="59a28cc7-016c-4405-a18f-2909e482b0b0">
      <Text>The crowd catches her again.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="91b8caa3-d4f4-4b97-a291-478419898ac2">
      <Text>The hands return.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="7e6b47b7-d19b-473b-9796-bfcebe5710ca">
      <Text>The current takes her.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="eb4c70d5-8101-4b76-93be-ec260ee2e931">
      <Text>And Jaz disappears into the churn, one more body in the machine, anonymous and free and exactly where she belongs.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="61865837-0f3b-4c00-8e3e-4bbc810a857e">
      <Text>HOLD on the pit from above—a writhing mass of humanity, somewhere in there a girl who was eating lemon chicken with her family two hours ago, now lost in a sea of strangers who know her better than her parents ever will.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="a1d76c50-9857-4880-a648-a66468fedc39">
      <SceneProperties Length="5/8" Page="31" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="KEVIN">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. MCCORT TOWNHOUSE - MASTER SUITE - NIGHT</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="216b1a81-ed7d-49b3-bc09-0e9ebbe2c5f8">
      <Text>3:45 AM glows red from the nightstand clock.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="c7f68c5e-a0fe-4819-bb7d-dff72f38735d">
      <Text>KEVIN's eyes snap open.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="e2bbb788-63fa-4b19-b32a-18b377dfdc19">
      <Text>He's still in his dress shirt. Wrinkled now. The Patek has left an imprint on his cheek from sleeping on his wrist.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="bfbbd9a4-9084-4e0f-91f9-8a1930880a9a">
      <Text>He blinks. Orients. Looks at the clock again.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="4c073b4d-f4be-4d1e-98a0-d0060b4cedec">
      <Text>Looks over at Janet.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="3a7c4ce5-cdaa-4c50-a5c2-c108bbaf165b">
      <Text>She's on her side, facing him, her makeup is perfection. The covers pulled up to her shoulder. Her hair fans across the pillow in a perfect halo—still damp from the shower. The picture of peaceful, obedient sleep. An angel resting after a long day of being his wife.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="5a1642fd-35e1-4ad9-a3de-53afb41aa1c2">
      <Text>Kevin smiles. Soft. Proprietary.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="4892d52d-2ad3-47b7-b37f-c9963cbd565c">
      <Text>He looks at the clock again.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="55698b64-ca6d-4d86-bd75-b746730e85fe">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="9a6e6ab1-40af-4d74-a587-eee6381a7a02">
      <Text>(under his breath)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="89c96f8c-d3f9-4141-a215-c214e1cbc5d9">
      <Text>Fuck it. Close enough.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="293c654d-f429-4625-ac92-26a8f87e4f56">
      <Text>He slides out of bed, Janet doesn't stir. She's learned not to even if she was awake.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="785d6927-8168-4687-a364-a03383c71246">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="32" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. MASTER CLOSET - CONTINUOUS</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="36ef348d-e19b-420f-96bb-4d5bc600d102">
      <Text>A walk-in the size of some Manhattan apartments. Kevin moves to his section—everything organized by color, by season, by function. He strips off the wrinkled dress shirt, pulls on compression gear, then sweats. Lululemon. The expensive men's line that pretends it's not Lululemon.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="a3f1b031-8836-4803-a2e0-cbd2cc9e482b">
      <Text>His gym bag is pre-packed. It's always pre-packed. His garment bag hangs ready on a hook—tomorrow's suit, tomorrow's shirt, tomorrow's tie. He grabs both.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="e5b88493-db68-41af-b30f-3dd7afff4445">
      <SceneProperties Length="5/8" Page="32" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="KEVIN">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. MCCORT TOWNHOUSE - HALLWAY - CONTINUOUS</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="8eab8376-a6c0-47e2-b284-8578c34fde0b">
      <Text>Kevin pads down the hall in his socks, bags over his shoulder.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="6a6d59b6-786a-483f-80e1-50da16b59053">
      <Text>He passes Jaz's door. Closed. Dark underneath. Good girl. Sleeping. Resting up for more academic excellence.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="48a1972c-38af-41c2-897d-b381ddade72c">
      <Text>He passes Jamie's door.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="4e7c75d6-2c05-47e2-9371-caada805bd4c">
      <Text>Light glows from underneath. Faint, but unmistakable.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="c92c2a4b-cfb5-45b8-9bb6-d31e5fda5f11">
      <Text>Kevin pauses. Checks his watch. 3:47 AM.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="3ebfec7d-56f6-4688-a23e-020f7ba92d0f">
      <Text>A knowing smirk spreads across his face.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="d2ebb888-10ff-4e96-9a44-9010990cbae8">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="8ca0147b-3974-4db0-9eda-aad7e1c84e3f">
      <Text>(to himself, approving)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="86700575-92ea-440e-9532-419a785af916">
      <Text>That's my boy.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="c51bbcc5-6ce5-4f98-9623-cfae369965e5">
      <Text>He shakes his head, amused. Proud, even.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="d2376602-fda0-425a-84ac-23fafcb6fc23">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="cbb36514-2412-4297-a8c6-3146e7ed7439">
      <Text>(murmuring)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="d680dcf1-22d3-485b-bc16-ece2d61f4293">
      <Text>Video chatting with some hot young thing. Attaboy.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="b793008b-4c0c-4b57-b477-699def487639">
      <Text>He moves on, leaving his son to what he imagines are adolescent digital conquests.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="90914959-801c-48ba-8d2b-e3d4c695c99d">
      <SceneProperties Length="4/8" Page="33" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="SINATRA">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. JAMIE'S BEDROOM - SAME TIME</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="073d23ba-36f3-4bd4-98e9-18971c8f0772">
      <Text>Six monitors glow in the darkness.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="2cfb3ea7-a7a6-43b5-9c4b-6da122d92063">
      <Text>JAMIE sits in his chair—an ergonomic throne with built-in speakers that cost more than most people's first car. From those speakers, barely above a whisper, but with perfect clarity, FRANK SINATRA croons:</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="409c7dad-7f09-44ff-acef-603f342ebe9e">
      <Text>SINATRA (V.O.)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="681c2f68-5775-4c6d-82b3-df7a80a3728f">
      <Text>(singing)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="cc88394e-d8be-4fd9-80f8-84e9fb2a4b11">
      <Text>"...Fly me to the moon, let me play among the stars..."</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="9a4b91c6-50c9-4c4e-968c-bf9feef3395b">
      <Text>Jamie isn't listening. Not really. It's ambient. Background noise for the work.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="e28cf95f-fc09-4b43-ac13-30c349ce6195">
      <Text>On screen: spreadsheets. Bank records. Corporate filings. A forensic accountant's fever dream.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="affff31e-d3da-4755-b018-25cea694461a">
      <Text>His eyes move across columns of numbers. His fingers tap occasionally—highlighting, cross-referencing, building connections his father can't see.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="52490f5b-b801-4815-be4d-bc88e8032df5">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="33" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. MCCORT TOWNHOUSE - KITCHEN - CONTINUOUS</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="39951a25-a9ac-449b-b1a6-b188b00061f3">
      <Text>Kevin moves through the dark kitchen with the confidence of ownership. He grabs his thermos from the built- in coffee station— a Miele that grinds, brews, and dispenses on a preset timer. His morning blend. Ready and waiting.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="b70c9d00-a16b-4761-a068-660f88b2f0af">
      <Text>He takes a sip. Perfect.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="43c552a1-2cce-4165-9c06-2b8e46c3989d">
      <Text>One last survey of his kingdom. The marble. The copper.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="d246828d-2923-4bbc-b1d4-164ec27937e1">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="33" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="KEVIN">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. MCCORT TOWNHOUSE - FOYER - CONTINUOUS</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="6c9b9ded-1e20-45d4-8ade-407f2fe8516c">
      <Text>The lilies on the console table in the foyer— slightly askew, he notices, one fallen over. Huh. Raises a judgmental eyebrow. He doesn't fix them. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="61185ada-373f-4575-97c4-d3aae99f3f5d">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="bbb51d0a-42f0-4b56-9e05-9e840762fc7f">
      <Text>(to his phone)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="b7886207-b80c-4283-9f92-fc84720fc6fa">
      <Text>Siri, make a note to knock another point off Maria’s Christmas bonus for the sloppy lilies.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="fe8b82ca-0161-4ae3-9149-ecc9ebadd309">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="34" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>EXT. MCCORT TOWNHOUSE - CONTINUOUS</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="6c55e0a9-6c3c-44e9-a1f8-b783174fc3a5">
      <Text>Kevin steps out into the pre-dawn dark. The city is quiet. That rare hour when even New York holds its breath.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="caa46a4d-56c9-4ae2-99a7-9163f1d09902">
      <Text>At the curb: a black Lincoln Continental. Engine running. Headlights off.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="2f4f70de-2c99-419a-921b-0494ee2866c2">
      <Text>Not Emmanuel this time. A different driver. They rotate.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="a6527c5a-cea5-4ab2-b8f2-1541e890164c">
      <Text>Kevin approaches. The rear door opens from inside.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="03c81b68-06c7-4efa-8577-358f115ddb73">
      <Text>He slides in. The door closes.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="7acb0a51-c7ad-4638-923c-8eab77359a82">
      <SceneProperties Length="4/8" Page="34" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="DRIVER">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="KEVIN">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. TOWN CAR - CONTINUOUS</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="7cb66ff8-f85f-4ae1-b3bc-adb9a1a63e54">
      <Text>Kevin settles into the leather. Sets his bags beside him. Checks his phone—emails already, even at this hour.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="0b22d72d-9e3c-46c1-8f25-4e87205c642a">
      <Text>KEVIN </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="cbfd513f-82fb-4168-b7f8-552e5e147fb0">
      <Text>(to the driver, not looking up)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="c9fde4a6-e597-466a-93f9-e1e14cf40d40">
      <Text>Morning Manny. Equinox. Columbus Circle.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="65411dc2-f410-485f-affa-efa104bb75e1">
      <Text>DRIVER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="fd4b9550-419e-49ea-9874-50312003a26a">
      <Text>Yes, sir.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="3ef7342c-a342-48b8-8264-9da629e8b439">
      <Text>The car pulls away from the curb.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="e209f5d1-1728-4ae7-a475-6c59d060cac7">
      <Text>He sips his coffee.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="4535ebc6-2350-4a12-998d-95b0effdd24c">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="a6d90ff2-f91a-4ce1-aa3e-62d911bc8671">
      <Text>(to himself, satisfied)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="50b532a6-9a50-4e23-a747-86b1b50015d7">
      <Text>Gonna be a good day.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="dc7e87d6-9f4e-4d1a-8aee-5cfbe34e5867">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 2/8" Page="34" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="JAZ">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TINY">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. ABANDONED SUBWAY STATION - BACKSTAGE DOOR - NIGHT</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="f9b1c42e-61f4-4431-b138-a3d4fac579c5">
      <Text>JAZ emerges from the pit like Venus from the Tsunami.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="82e62a84-fdcc-4ce8-b677-4c535dffd9a6">
      <Text>Her hair is matted with sweat—hers, others'. The black leather harness crisscrossing her bare torso. Her fishnets have new tears, Rainbow booty short sequins sparkling. One boot is still unlaced. Smeared eyeliner. Bruises forming on her ribs from elbows she never saw coming.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="61ac1fdc-086f-4ab6-80bf-15b12f0b1f07">
      <Text>She looks just the kind of destroyed she wanted.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="453ab35c-ac63-4d8b-978d-6af3e809af85">
      <Text>She looks perfect.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="9fab7a2f-4bc1-4c9d-aa7b-e46fba5ca47d">
      <Text>The backstage door is guarded by TINY— who is not tiny. Six-five, 280, head like a cinder block, wearing a vest made of what appears to be repurposed seatbelts. His face is a topographical map of old fights.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="e1538bb6-8d04-4635-8fdd-6401155f03b6">
      <Text>He sees her coming.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="f9e88a6f-2f57-41c6-8189-d7298aa0d82c">
      <Text>TINY</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="73a00053-e8b2-4534-bec6-a26913d6faea">
      <Text>(holding something up)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="b3d01d25-504d-43ab-b93b-cff466e9672d">
      <Text>Caught this in the pit. Third song.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="196ac7ed-2c46-4635-af0f-b3b2d42a6a41">
      <Text>Her leather jacket. The patches. The studs. The hand-stitched middle finger.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="5dfa3d60-5f54-4c32-b9bb-7c3746d92c51">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="25903b8d-e981-4a23-bce2-28b86467ad92">
      <Text>Tiny. You're a goddamn gentleman.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="ac04af18-4dbd-492a-a675-5079c19f3e38">
      <Text>TINY</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="1294dbf6-26da-4203-97d7-a2b500e0e4f6">
      <Text>I know how precious it is to you. Someone was trying to wear it. I explained that was a bad idea.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="48fb5e5f-4083-44ef-a08f-583d49027a50">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="7fd0db2d-2043-4c81-8869-bb8890c401ba">
      <Text>If you truly love something set it free, and If if comes back it’s truly yours.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="edbb4e02-9fac-4d65-8ca8-dbc3c7f02c84">
      <Text>TINY</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="6eadede2-7fa4-4b48-87dc-3b51a0411985">
      <Text>Everyone knows your plumage, Pheonix.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="574b38ea-0567-4298-89f6-1ad1a9899f25">
      <Text>She hands him the clear plastic cup she's holding—some toxic amalgamation of bottom-shelf vodka and energy drink that could probably strip paint. He takes it without question.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="2d181c90-0441-49de-a07c-0effd7c8c51c">
      <Text>She slips her arms into the jacket. The leather is cold from being away from her body. It brushes across her chest and she BRISTLES— a sharp intake of breath as the chill hits her pierced nipples.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="67f38587-6f82-4274-ba0f-fc38ca22990b">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="dca88788-ac12-4a9f-a07a-a0642107b7a9">
      <Text>Fuck. Every time.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="c4059dc4-dc5b-4469-8928-6f3b5dcd8ac2">
      <Text>TINY</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="7df9d39e-f087-4229-b447-cb4f6126cfbc">
      <Text>You could zip it.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="34793f79-191d-4a59-9b67-0aaa63eb477e">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="fb91310f-1141-4876-971b-aa268e99f675">
      <Text>Where's the fun in that?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="2e78046e-d128-4b9a-8cf9-c43ad4a5f156">
      <Text>She doesn't zip it. Doesn't even consider it. She kisses Tiny on his cinder block cheek, reclaims her drink, and slips through the door.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="78fb8393-9ca2-49ce-b3f9-bb9f612e3b87">
      <SceneProperties Length="4 5/8" Page="36" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="CHUCKLES">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="COKE LADY #1">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="DECLAN">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="GREEN HAIR GIRL">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="JAZ">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. BACKSTAGE - CONTINUOUS</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="5887786b-bccb-4ab1-b0f8-20ca50caf773">
      <Text>If the pit was a cathedral, backstage is the confessional. Where sins happen.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="b24236b9-e8e2-425d-9f00-ec43f6391d7b">
      <Text>The room is a concrete bunker dressed up with stolen furniture and Christmas lights. Couches that have seen everything. Carpet that's given up asking questions.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="46fbe001-50a3-40cc-9916-15395ad7d69a">
      <Text>At the center: a coffee table. On it: a PILE of cocaine. Not lines—a pile. A small mountain. Viagra kickers scatter like little rocks on the ski slopes. The Everest of bad decisions. Two women— COKE WOMEN OF THE NIGHT in the most affectionate possible sense— are curled around it like it's a campfire, taking turns with a rolled twenty, murmuring to each other between snorts.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="869f6f75-6118-4245-bf8f-0ddc4156915e">
      <Text>In one corner: the DRUMMER, still shirtless, still drenched, has some young GUY pressed against the wall and is going at him with enthusiasm. The guy's expression suggests he cannot believe his luck. His shirt is somewhere. His pants around his ankles.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="2901ca8d-9b3b-4c1d-8c5a-812fe19bfc6d">
      <Text>In another corner: the GUITARIST is passed out cold on a loveseat, mouth open, dead to the world. A GIRL with green hair and a nose ring has her hand down the front of his leather pants, stroking lazily, nothing happening. He’s out and shows no signs of cooperating.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="de1238f4-9eca-43ce-bb8b-35cd8b15922a">
      <Text>GREEN HAIR GIRL</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="0e29cd2a-2718-4ff4-ba7a-6c5840336dd1">
      <Text>(to no one)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="e8902061-2cc4-4d54-87f2-b1bf1d3a36f1">
      <Text>Come on, wake up. I saw you play. I thought you had stamina.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="e5e07fc0-767f-45c8-bf47-e06cdcd31806">
      <Text>The guitarist snores in response.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="b334998a-ca16-4683-8d67-0d267854e1ed">
      <Text>And in the back corner, on a ratty throne of a chair that might have once been in a dentist's office: DECLAN.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="6eb17eea-cd28-4c61-9fe9-79cebcb2657c">
      <Text>He's traded the G-string for a silk kimono—black with red dragons, hanging open, revealing everything and concealing nothing. His liberty spikes are wilting slightly from sweat. He's got a cigarette in one hand, whiskey in the other.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="8c6830ef-e197-4fb8-883d-a4a83a02412a">
      <Text>And between his legs: a GIRL. Early twenties. Immaculate makeup. Designer ripped jeans. A leather jacket that still has the Nordstrom tags energy. She's a "punk" the way a Madison ave exec is a punk— all aesthetic, no anarchy.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="0fc6c159-3f7c-4864-8861-03659a7526ee">
      <Text>She's on her knees. Declan's kimono is pushed aside. Her head bobs rhythmically.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="a8690ed9-0a02-4127-bb30-f8ac5392e408">
      <Text>Declan watches the room like a king surveying his court. Bored, almost. Another Tuesday.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="2f559eb5-990b-4be2-b92d-32b605cb687d">
      <Text>His eyes find Jaz the moment she enters.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="dfaa3b76-7594-45d0-872b-11c9ca12d698">
      <Text>A FIGURE steps into her path—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="b61aa2a8-3435-42b4-bfb1-fe76f6a43411">
      <Text>CHUCKLES. The band's "manager." Mid-thirties but looks fifty, coked out of his mind, jaw grinding, sweat stains under his vintage band tee. He's got a clipboard he's not using and an energy that screams "I peaked in 2009."</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="42488d0e-9536-42bd-9954-cf853f014a18">
      <Text>CHUCKLES</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="8fba6e99-846b-4e5d-ab3a-9d8aeef19ca9">
      <Text>(way too fast, too loud)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="ac5524d8-d0ef-4c88-b330-b10be23ce337">
      <Text>Jaz! Jazzy! Phoenix! Whatever! Great show! Great show! You were incredible up there the crowd fucking LOVED it hey listen I got some people I want you to meet some label people well not LABEL label but like they know label distribution adjacent people—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="76dc2e7f-1e65-4dd3-8563-3f0ee4f2e026">
      <Text>He's physically trying to position himself between her and Declan's corner. Blocking the view. Protecting his meal ticket from seeing—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="26475a60-6718-4ba7-963e-ee379ba227c9">
      <Text>Jaz looks past him. Sees exactly what's happening. Her expression doesn't change.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="5e793bb9-d1cf-43e1-9273-27bcb51e5ec1">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="df40be0d-d80c-4d42-b671-0c0fd2edb15c">
      <Text>(flat)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="1da068f2-9614-4175-aa12-f2906dde4659">
      <Text>Chuckles. Move.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="6667d4d0-59b3-47ff-b3d3-97770d9d98a5">
      <Text>CHUCKLES</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="fd35278c-3ccc-4660-954a-f85dc389e570">
      <Text>—because I think there's a real opportunity here for cross-platform synergy if we can just—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="d855aee9-e067-4fe2-aaf8-2f2ca32f6d4c">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="d6e37b0a-2d1f-4bac-9818-95ca18bd45c6">
      <Text>I can see him, Chuckles. I don't care.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="1cd1aab8-a33c-48dc-8582-293e42ee07b5">
      <Text>She steps around him like he's furniture.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="4b96b702-150e-45c1-87a9-aa8c131b0d4c">
      <Text>Chuckles deflates. He really thought that was going to work.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="92f92b73-9579-4702-b96a-f1879da4a499">
      <Text>Jaz drifts toward the coffee table. The coke ladies look up, recognize her, and wordlessly make space. One offers the rolled twenty. Jaz waves it off.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="2cea8707-630b-4f54-9eba-064a78542ea6">
      <Text>Instead, she extends her pinky nail—painted black, chipped—and scoops up a bump's worth. One practiced snort. A sharp inhale. She blinks twice as it hits.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="80366363-8249-4f3e-9dad-c96b397344f8">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="d4419b65-daec-412c-a1c3-065b37cb6d08">
      <Text>(to the coke lady)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="51400df6-876a-467e-a1e7-d47dac917927">
      <Text>Good batch.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="17fdb3fd-2292-4f62-8333-2c7942b4ba4d">
      <Text>COKE Lady #1</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="5f32134f-63ec-4854-a769-0b5caf85aded">
      <Text>yeah! Great!</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="870e2a65-ecd5-4122-89d8-2c6d451d4158">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="732b154e-8794-4d22-b4d3-af0a098f1ec4">
      <Text>(nodding at Declan)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="4aa1233e-2fc1-4580-a052-2f14b866c04a">
      <Text>It’s his uncles supply.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="3e3b5e33-bbbc-4e83-a767-18ee81957f21">
      <Text>Her fingers find a couple small glass vials near the pile— guest bumps, party favor, road supplies. She palms them, slips them into her jacket pocket. No one objects. No one cares.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="089dc7c6-3f5b-4216-8c8f-9927241cdc80">
      <Text>DECLAN (O.S.)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="2664e19c-c854-4193-9b85-3cc7e7802f87">
      <Text>Oi.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="a6d30064-965d-465f-8052-b62bb9e318a5">
      <Text>She doesn’t bother to turn.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="235fc795-b8e4-4f1f-aa1d-3553fdb15302">
      <Text>Declan has extricated himself from the girl's mouth. She looks annoyed—interrupted mid-task, lipstick smeared. Declan is already standing, tying the kimono loosely, his erection visibly tenting the silk.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="45279764-d9ec-4741-9727-00def0c6e400">
      <Text>He crosses to Jaz. The Nordstrom punk chick stays on her knees, confused about what to do with herself.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="4eaf0453-db8f-4ca3-8d25-8afb14a1ac35">
      <Text>DECLAN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="2cc7c777-c767-4f7e-8a32-fcdb25d59005">
      <Text>(to the girl, dismissive)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="69aed669-0f4e-4e9c-be33-a24fd2632817">
      <Text>Fuck off for a minute.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="8d48a4a5-f42c-4a9d-b76b-48c4261541a0">
      <Text>The girl fucks off.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="2fcdefa7-531f-480f-bb33-cec254be6d08">
      <Text>Declan reaches Jaz, spins her around by the shoulder to face him. Not rough. Just entitled. Like he's earned something.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="f9586fd6-ec54-4194-a71e-cd8bdee2f077">
      <Text>The kimono is barely closed. His situation is... apparent.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="43492ab8-a862-4188-aa5b-a1b905bd45b8">
      <Text>DECLAN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="db48dfa3-e02e-4844-b192-bbbb908ed2cb">
      <Text>(grinning)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="28519b46-240d-4e0a-baf4-29e9ef3c3813">
      <Text>You were good up there tonight.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="3dfb5779-e632-4c2b-96f4-f07bba5b7cdb">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="1c83b9e7-b922-4dec-bff9-3d911a4bfc0f">
      <Text>I know.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="73298269-2ec1-4a7e-a142-a381b4973ee6">
      <Text>DECLAN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="4d0f9a43-fa9d-47a5-a6ee-b0d6a16d8d04">
      <Text>Crowd went fucking mental when you kissed me.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="5e94f3da-e44a-4c85-a5d5-5c8081a88634">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="e730e69a-fd79-4456-831e-4c8e7924c170">
      <Text>They went mental when I kissed the other one too.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="7662e878-ed2c-4883-9cac-83955373dafa">
      <Text>DECLAN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="6d1361a5-f8c8-4ab3-82ff-c9bd0bfb64ed">
      <Text>(ignoring that)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="029b4785-47d4-4dee-b9bb-5d641a0d625a">
      <Text>Chuckles booked us a show in Detroit next week. Real venue. Real money.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="69713045-eea1-458f-b78a-2c046441fc8b">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="c125ccb3-0f75-46e3-9235-817947fa2495">
      <Text>Congratulations.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="c2b5cf7d-f7f1-443c-91ad-630001a25f9b">
      <Text>DECLAN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="3f5d4d4e-7a40-49e6-b087-106760068947">
      <Text>(leaning closer, his hand cupping her breast under her open jacket)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="d41a338e-3146-4f27-90fb-05fbfb9b4ca7">
      <Text>If you're sweet enough to me... maybe I'll let you dance on stage for us there. Give the Midwest a taste of what they're missing.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="5edb54e6-c51e-484b-a8f4-53a2c788c616">
      <Text>He says it like it's an offer she should be grateful for. A gift. Access to him.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="a854c11c-241c-4fbf-b5e4-3d77c23f3afe">
      <Text>Jaz looks at him. Holds his gaze.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="6d6a1d77-f819-44b0-b7a6-b03bdf5cf3f7">
      <Text>Then she leans in. Close. Her lips brush his ear— just barely, just enough to make him shiver.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="42c6f6f9-c4c8-4e49-a4bb-c482670e07f6">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="4401da29-5bcf-4942-b258-77983a727a54">
      <Text>(whispering)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="ba923fc8-5e72-4701-a531-cb787c3d82b9">
      <Text>Yeah? How sweet?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="47a9e866-0fcc-4e28-8e37-7e2674676ffa">
      <Text>Her hand finds his erection wrapped in silk. Wraps around him. He's hard. Very hard.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="1fbba0ab-3063-4171-858a-8f4183fcf27e">
      <Text>A moan escapes his lips before he can stop it.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="cef66ef5-60f3-4f19-92d1-6ea381556448">
      <Text>She giggles. Low. Wicked.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="f16c4e9e-cf54-414e-8948-5bc0f8d9e378">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="d942b4ce-e9d8-4fcb-86df-d622df3ab1a0">
      <Text>(still whispering, stroking slowly)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="65913040-ad8c-489d-8857-82df8bce51d4">
      <Text>We both know you have a very nice cock. And I enjoyed it last time.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="a6632288-f258-4145-b87e-7f49d51a9bb8">
      <Text>Her grip tightens. His breath catches.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="8c7786b0-00af-4dd5-848a-f6b960eb8ad3">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="0c09675a-5e67-49cb-80c6-c87a37d63950">
      <Text>Even if it was too... brief for my taste.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="3a55fcbe-621b-4c3e-87d5-590fb35fbc05">
      <Text>She strokes again. Once. Twice. His hips start to move involuntarily.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="abd5c156-1547-45b4-b284-b02ae81a1b20">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="b76f766b-92ee-4a4f-b278-b77e43ff4baf">
      <Text>But it's just a cock.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="3e41aeaa-e517-4bee-b814-ba2b33e1f96e">
      <Text>She releases him. Steps back. Leaves him standing there, tented and wanting.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="71608831-6a8f-46a4-bfe3-39c1a6d3ee9a">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="e4a99145-d4aa-41d1-82b6-82ab85ca3447">
      <Text>(normal volume now, sweet smile)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="8416f672-f4ce-42f0-9bfa-14a433461917">
      <Text>And absolutely not worth traveling for.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="79993b2e-2cc2-45f6-9abc-f64825b42829">
      <Text>His face cycles through confusion, arousal, and indignation in about two seconds.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="61bc571a-b932-4ef8-98c8-f6eca9ff5b52">
      <Text>DECLAN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="c23478ab-60ac-4b24-b53b-75fdbb84e731">
      <Text>You're a fucking cunt.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="0573790d-3629-463b-81af-e6004c54347f">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="76fcb04b-44c6-459e-a688-18b566c2f447">
      <Text>(already heading for the door)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="b92d971a-c21b-485a-ba71-4a0f8647dbcd">
      <Text>I'm a lot of things. But first and foremost... I am always my own.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="8506f248-ef2d-4748-9ef4-bfe6b06145ac">
      <Text>She looks back over her shoulder. The jacket still open. The harness. The chaos. The girl who had a family dinner six hours ago.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="f3969c65-80ff-4cc1-bf41-d9815e12db26">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="eecc3886-ad01-46d7-bb31-a0d6bbc46493">
      <Text>And I have a game to win.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="5a73924f-bf98-4871-9a97-722a35e3479e">
      <Text>And she's gone.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="7dc81061-8661-48d2-85c6-1b43c29a381b">
      <Text>Declan stands there. Blue-balled and furious.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="356be8ff-a3ce-48c5-b287-ee02c29deaf3">
      <SceneProperties Length="2 3/8" Page="40" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="KEVIN">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MARCUS">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. EQUINOX - COLUMBUS CIRCLE - WEIGHT ROOM - DAWN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="ad704b5c-e2a9-4853-a1ad-681b214a6e77">
      <Text>The gym is nearly empty at this hour. Just the obsessives. The compulsives. The men who think arriving before sunrise is a personality trait.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="37179381-efe7-4331-90a5-4cd287b5b64d">
      <Text>KEVIN is on the bench press. His spotter stands over him.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="ea59f65d-a542-401a-943f-f21085d40372">
      <Text>MARCUS (32) is a sculpture of a human being. Shoulders like cannonballs. Waist like a wasp. The kind of body that takes four hours a day and a complicated relationship with chicken breast. He's got a fitted Equinox trainer polo that's working overtime.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="5285d269-385e-44c3-a153-3c075de56ebd">
      <Text>Kevin pushes through a rep. Marcus guides the bar. Not that Kevin needs it—this weight is well within his range—but having a spotter is part of the experience. The service.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="5538a162-c775-4629-acff-168b642fa3a4">
      <Text>MARCUS</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="278c81eb-8d45-451c-b9aa-40e6ad3a4982">
      <Text>—and I'm not even kidding bro, she just grabbed it. Right through my shorts. No warning. Just full palm on my balls like she's checking a melon for ripeness.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="9c57f657-050b-4453-8349-b81c86cca4cd">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="d45c9130-c882-4749-862b-43ac05857024">
      <Text>(exhaling through a rep)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="8d80250d-28fc-416b-9d63-a54967db9e8b">
      <Text>Uh huh.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="5e8dbf19-0e6d-4286-9c9c-bd36cc9baa46">
      <Text>MARCUS</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="9856cc2a-8a14-4c0e-bc33-f526181c3115">
      <Text>It's like... I get it, okay? I'm in shape. I work on this.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="3d7b852c-f9e8-4f53-890f-fccb0a2eb20b">
      <Text>(gesturing at himself)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="01d376bd-d406-4320-9593-e151839a658b">
      <Text>But do they think I don't have a mind? Like there's nothing going on up here?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="508e14e4-bdb4-4820-a66a-36301baa21fb">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="c830c1c7-4a78-4e53-bfac-f35f9f9eb9cd">
      <Text>(pushing)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="9bcc74d1-c458-4bdf-90b8-c6c1d57e1b77">
      <Text>Right.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="67b28a50-e636-4d00-b674-76164528d023">
      <Text>MARCUS</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="718f549c-0374-4bf6-8a79-237d307c0025">
      <Text>These Upper West Side wives, man. They book me for "personal training" and then it's all—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="88f853d5-1328-429d-9271-b0c1bd8a99d6">
      <Text>(mimicking a breathy voice)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="a90dc09f-f4cb-4969-b9ea-9031e5200f3d">
      <Text>—"Marcus, can you spot me on the hip thrusts? Marcus, I think my glutes are tight, can you stretch them?"</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="de987012-ac5e-418b-a06f-9cba690102db">
      <Text>Kevin racks the bar. Sits up. Towels his face.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="bd6b61eb-37a3-447a-8af7-fe2ed9251235">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="0823c6a5-fa3e-4c5b-921b-b13d6350de3a">
      <Text>Sounds rough.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="73b2b20e-68fc-49ce-a08b-317e6739a727">
      <Text>MARCUS</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="6b20df67-219b-4099-b1f8-b75bc2222b1f">
      <Text>(not catching the tone)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="f55f6980-f713-4c27-9bb0-30e79ed2499b">
      <Text>It IS rough. It's like... I'm a whole person.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="325fdb80-fc5d-45e3-a9fd-2dbcd303d18c">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="5b536a3f-0fd6-48d2-89b4-8ac57da32916">
      <Text>(genuinely surprised)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="2d3b383a-d380-4a51-9ac8-95ae22508672">
      <Text>Yeah?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="ba2bddd5-31db-4824-8cae-23ff89d9a730">
      <Text>MARCUS</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="994e19b1-c2f1-4b87-bae4-b5756940e9a7">
      <Text>I read this book on braiding sweetgrass. It's about indigenous wisdom and like... plants and shit. It was beautiful. Made me cry. Twice.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d46284ee-8108-48d4-af43-5e5ada0e0098">
      <Text>Kevin blinks. Doesn't know what to do with that information. Goes back for another set.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="5bdb998d-e8af-4f4e-8715-42b551fa1d6c">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="c2fed5ed-3d41-414f-b684-998b19871687">
      <Text>Huh.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="bb64facd-2df2-41ba-a44b-5efa2b7306bc">
      <Text>MARCUS</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="939a241e-f41a-46aa-be78-ee3a7ecad918">
      <Text>You think any of these women ask me about that shit when their husbands are at the office?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="6e4b7cb5-a23c-4d72-8230-83d83bceafd8">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="93a24e21-78d8-4eb8-a789-d9a38b60e766">
      <Text>(pushing)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="3d5333a0-c24e-4e5e-9995-541104e3d4c2">
      <Text>That's a shame.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="009ee935-f77d-4060-b264-97c6dff21384">
      <Text>MARCUS</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="bfd8cf56-3c61-4f3d-87c3-be34f3e09dbe">
      <Text>It IS a shame. I'm more than a body.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="62ef1809-b602-4dbe-ad6d-d8ad80c1c509">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="a5337911-11ba-4886-98b0-1a50073ecd32">
      <Text>Don't get me wrong. I'm balls deep in like half of them. These dickhead husbands working eighty-hour weeks, ignoring their wives— I'm providing a community service.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="188cac56-d444-428f-a56c-c923ab2e8162">
      <Text>Kevin nods. Keeps pushing. The irony sails past him at cruising altitude.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="6a7023b3-3be3-44a7-880f-35ac16e6bff1">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="a9f37311-3cf5-453a-b4db-7e52344c5db2">
      <Text>(finishing the set)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="69aac41d-2f22-4cbe-81c9-354dd08162c7">
      <Text>People can be self-absorbed.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="59ec26a0-9e97-4429-87af-e077a1bd25af">
      <Text>Kevin checks his watch. An Apple Ultra he only wears at the gym because serious athletes take data seriously.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="949879f6-264a-48af-af1e-e46e7b7b410a">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="0d12daa8-6fe5-423c-ae34-16114e91f4ed">
      <Text>I gotta wrap up. Got the table booked at five.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="55997c6b-c49f-4973-bd3e-fb1084d8fcd8">
      <Text>MARCUS</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="ea89f1c2-3187-4e56-a0ba-4de76bea77d6">
      <Text>Huh? Oh yeah. Katya IS the best. Those hands. That pressure.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="7d8b3a07-d8d2-4c9d-a51f-446e95e1b17b">
      <Text>(beat, professional)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="9145fc7f-55bc-4b61-837b-49e05c412e42">
      <Text>Good workout today. Same time Thursday?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="ecc15031-f330-404f-9814-4243ddf8bb93">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="c2338e1e-08ee-41dc-8dc1-a18344103835">
      <Text>(grabbing his towel)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="e219c32d-cf68-42ab-9f2f-9cbaef8e1ea4">
      <Text>Lock it in.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="38a3a9fa-2595-4545-9f34-1599b7c85f3f">
      <Text>They do a complicated handshake that Kevin probably practiced.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="e778d79e-1794-4ec0-9aa5-7169a4f47849">
      <SceneProperties Length="1/8" Page="43" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. EQUINOX - SPA LEVEL - MOMENTS LATER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="58a40df3-d320-48ad-a317-6606f9d7f6dc">
      <Text>A hallway of soft lighting and softer music. The smell of eucalyptus and money.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="802facc1-4887-41eb-97a9-691d14ea3c09">
      <Text>Kevin pushes through a door marked PRIVATE TREATMENT ROOMS.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="388d9a43-7808-4257-b1a8-509fd8a5bd5f">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 2/8" Page="43" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="KATYA">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="KEVIN">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. MASSAGE ROOM - CONTINUOUS</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="bb141aae-35be-4f3d-8e91-281f702de69d">
      <Text>Dim. Warm. A massage table with a face cradle. Candles that cost more than most people's groceries.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="8f3da9da-54c5-42d8-95f5-dc56882481be">
      <Text>KATYA (40s, Eastern European, forearms like a longshoreman's) stands waiting. White uniform. Hair pulled back. Looks exactly like the brochure.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="273a6ac3-ffa8-4d80-ba14-6c490d559d97">
      <Text>KATYA</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="f7771b69-a1a5-4ada-abe1-6d9c9856034c">
      <Text>(accent)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="8a3db6ee-5c7c-4500-971c-4268048066a4">
      <Text>Mr. McCort. Early today.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="77ec492b-1c07-4b7f-8976-6e785a059dc2">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="0f30f5f1-f13a-46f4-9526-c76ad3f1240a">
      <Text>Big day ahead. Need to be loose.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="edefb8b9-c6ac-4c51-a684-92e3292f5f4d">
      <Text>Kevin's already stripping. No modesty. He's paying for this.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="86a00f3b-7262-4f6e-84d6-7538200f3bab">
      <Text>He settles onto the table. Face in the cradle. The sheet draped strategically across his lower back.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="82967ddc-a729-4412-a062-4da5a1667d01">
      <Text>Katya's hands find his shoulders. Strong. Professional. For now.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="24923b5a-f91c-405d-90e7-4e4dc7ff6411">
      <Text>KATYA</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="8e334c00-cd85-4533-8336-cba63413a53a">
      <Text>Tension here. Here. You carry stress in your trapezius.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="54afc277-78c2-44cc-a2c7-1ef70a30da5d">
      <Text>Kevin fidgets, big day, gotta get to work. He flips.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="b8cd2d4b-3561-478e-aa38-ccdd001bc142">
      <Text>He’s paying for this. And time is money.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="e83a2718-f290-496c-9f02-a2cd9b6fef26">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="220a42e8-db46-454b-9270-850d44014365">
      <Text>(brazen)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="0e26a365-20aa-4bc6-a833-8af03a55eb5d">
      <Text>Can we skip to the end. I got a lot on my plate this afternoon.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="f53e1d33-9548-4b57-9c39-c72849f523a6">
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d82818e8-2f62-4ec2-b4a0-6a29e1059302">
      <Text>She works down his chest. Methodical. Expert. The music swells slightly—some ambient spa playlist designed to make wealthy men feel they deserve this.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="963a91e7-11d0-4229-9607-e8f3e519c8ba">
      <Text>Kevin's breathing has changed. The sheet crumples on the floor.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="1a9b98c4-63fe-4916-94cc-09a6152be0b3">
      <Text>KATYA</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="1444e82c-d2eb-4498-9a6d-473e38038128">
      <Text>(clinical, almost bored)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="82361e3c-6f4b-45fd-a4a7-3dfab3a910c6">
      <Text>You tell me when.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="03c63972-c463-45f4-8b4f-608875b74b4b">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="50cc15f7-7578-4a7a-850b-82d3d91d9fe4">
      <Text>(eyes closed, voice tight)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="73248585-27c2-476b-9dbf-e1141beb07b2">
      <Text>Yeah... yeah, right there...</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="9c9a3e42-8fc5-4e43-ab77-c1715276fe37">
      <Text>The rhythm is evident. The transaction is clear.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="620405b1-2419-4d5f-9c13-47062aa8dc3c">
      <Text>KATYA</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="ab819a63-a7e7-4a6d-b240-5a11d11f14fa">
      <Text>(same flat tone)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="6f636c85-3934-4724-a676-c356a36b9c36">
      <Text>Breathe. Let go of stress.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="00ea3c23-809d-4e09-ad7f-a491cd5d1d9a">
      <Text>Kevin lets go of stress.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="59300c85-224a-4732-9bd1-6cd727caa5b3">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 1/8" Page="44" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="JAZ">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MR. CHEN">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>EXT. CHINATOWN - PRE-DAWN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="01490f76-ffe8-4618-b2e6-f0eb70e15df8">
      <Text>The streets are empty except for the things that run at this hour: garbage trucks grinding through their routes, a few delivery vans, rats that don't bother to hide.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="05da20fa-1ff2-4423-ac72-e9c3fd774713">
      <Text>JAZ walks through, jacket zipped halfway now— a concession to context, not modesty. The harness peeks out. The boots echo on wet pavement.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="7cc66544-951f-41c9-9604-d913ff5329bf">
      <Text>She stops at a door.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="a4f0c79b-f3c5-43ca-a2ec-145fce1674b9">
      <Text>WANG'S AUTHENTIC NOODLE reads the faded sign. The windows are dark, covered with newspaper from the inside. Health code rating: not posted. Ambiance: "go away."</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="09fe68c4-a702-42ac-b5c6-52e0c894e905">
      <Text>She knocks. Three times. Pause. Two more.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="4909a3c3-fd1f-4d40-8b64-2af926466ccf">
      <Text>The locks start clicking. Three of them. Then a chain. Then a deadbolt that sounds like it was installed during the Roosevelt administration. The first one.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="269c72ee-3253-437e-831c-1fabf03e996f">
      <Text>The door opens six inches.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="a76cdf0a-829c-4671-9690-f74c946feb88">
      <Text>MR. CHEN (70s, face like weathered leather, cigarette permanently fused to his lower lip) peers out. He looks at Jaz. Recognition flickers.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="6c513923-2ddc-4ec7-916c-4d11cce5381a">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="312d7fd9-2d70-4f86-a1c2-4deabce02ad9">
      <Text>Miss me?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="340c7acc-7200-4ff2-bb85-d817986a274c">
      <Text>MR. CHEN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="667082a0-1bcc-4072-abf3-52b4374100ab">
      <Text>(Cantonese accent, grumbling)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="b5c9c302-8713-420f-88dc-db9fbb59e68c">
      <Text>You take nine thousand dollar from Jimmy Fong last time. He very unhappy.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="66a777da-1ce7-4f1e-9bed-1710bd67c436">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="c927a429-4c4b-4b01-bfb7-847e81f9c566">
      <Text>Jimmy Fong plays like shit.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="34d8e3cc-e536-456e-a5b0-0183b86665b0">
      <Text>MR. CHEN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="1a3743e2-619a-418c-92a9-fd36de560e24">
      <Text>This is true. But still.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="ae515088-b98c-492e-bd79-baf07ea5d6b9">
      <Text>(opening the door wider, grudging)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="eea4e8d7-e63e-4041-a0b6-8d8f3caf0bf3">
      <Text>I cannot guarantee safety if you fleece these assholes again.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="b17642d7-8a90-44df-9949-e1d554300fee">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="23c17e9f-2276-49dd-8f1b-5075a835f9e0">
      <Text>(stepping inside)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="db3aa299-bb64-44aa-b69a-4ecbee90b970">
      <Text>Mr. Chen. When have I ever needed you to guarantee my safety?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="6696ea9a-3c9b-429f-80e7-9849bc0d233d">
      <Text>He grunts. Can't argue with that.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="d73a96d5-1d32-436d-aed4-54fa8739d587">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="45" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. WANG'S AUTHENTIC NOODLE - CONTINUOUS</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="87df4d5f-eeb1-49bf-82f7-81bdfa7b4b9d">
      <Text>Dark. The smell of decades of grease and something older. Stools upturned on the counter. A kitchen visible through a pass-through window.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="c1b97b41-d1e1-4076-b048-4306404c0761">
      <Text>And hanging in that window: fresh carcasses. Ducks, lacquered and gleaming. Pigs, split open, ribs like fingers. To a door that looks like a broom closet.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="ce7947f0-644f-4538-ad4d-f9a49a137127">
      <Text>It's not a broom closet.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="b5b12444-a37d-4bbd-9276-cc4a3fc9d453">
      <SceneProperties Length="3/8" Page="45" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. STAIRCASE - CONTINUOUS</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="a8f15f0f-e018-47f0-9cf4-5d46dfe529f8">
      <Text>Narrow. Steep. The walls are close enough to touch both sides.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="3c7c171e-55ee-4d19-bf1b-b5aab5289d05">
      <Text>The sounds rise to meet her: voices, laughter, the click of chips.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="a32668a2-ded8-4fd5-827f-757cbd25d241">
      <Text>At the bottom: a door. Old wood. Iron hardware. Its been here since this building was something else, in a century that's been dead a hundred years.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="dd7c94c5-3efd-4134-8425-3fd50f3baf4d">
      <Text>Mr. Chen pushes it open.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="6c63c46e-5d4d-4f9d-91fb-6268ccca0d9c">
      <SceneProperties Length="3 2/8" Page="45" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="BRAD">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="CHASE">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="HUNTER">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="JAZ">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="JIMMY FONG">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="SKYLER">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TANNER">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. BASEMENT POKER ROOM - CONTINUOUS</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="e45bc77d-fae1-495a-962c-a8a50e985974">
      <Text>Smoke. A fog of it. Cigars, cigarettes, and something sweeter underneath that no one's going to ask about.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="6a5e1035-7952-428f-97f8-2bb450be405c">
      <Text>The room is low-ceilinged, brick-walled, lit by hanging fixtures that might be originally gas lamps. A round table dominates the center, green felt worn smooth by generations of gamblers.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="7e961011-2fec-49b1-a5f6-b2dac26b7176">
      <Text>In the corners: the MUSCLE. Three of them. Chinese. Stone-faced. Not playing. Not talking. Just present. Their job is simple: make sure no one gets cute. The house gets its cut. Everyone leaves with the fingers they came in with.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="5cc18ab9-d6ba-4083-82a5-0425338a73b1">
      <Text>But the players—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="cdffbc60-6192-4613-92e9-761b3a2c8761">
      <Text>The players are not what you'd expect.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="8a5bece7-5908-4715-9b6f-2bddbc09f475">
      <Text>Six men around the table. And they are, the most punchable collection of finance bros ever assembled.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="08e9e139-035d-444e-b3f1-1102d709995f">
      <Text>BRAD, 30s, Patagonia vest over a dress shirt, no tie, hasn't slept. HUNTER, 30s, hair gel, collar popped, eyes chemically wide. SKYLER, 20s, looks like he was grown in a Goldman lab. CHASE, 30s, already sweating, already losing. TANNER, 30s, wearing a suit that cost more than some cars, tangerine pocket square.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="971581ca-0ee3-4bd0-9420-6fdbe938fdb1">
      <Text>And JIMMY FONG, 40s, actually Asian, actually from Chinatown, actually pissed about last time, is glaring at the door.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="abb03e55-ffb1-4e11-85d8-fe8479b4e8fb">
      <Text>The door where Jaz just appeared.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="fa731aec-935c-43a4-bb0c-a67fe5c2fbef">
      <Text>HUNTER spots her first.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d700671c-fbbe-44bc-bf90-75b20298ee83">
      <Text>He starts humming.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="b9ccfe61-6cef-401d-aaf6-3d9320441aaa">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="3249a88c-2548-4188-a0af-1269cd9e00fa">
      <Text>(humming)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="3bdd4782-eaf2-4511-93ed-931776db6f6e">
      <Text>Dun dun dun, dun da-dun, dun da-dun...</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="47179288-fc22-4547-a5f3-57afa9fc1979">
      <Text>The Imperial March. Darth Vader's theme.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="58a3b999-0f95-4c23-ad5e-270496cb8243">
      <Text>BRAD</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="474cf147-a1f8-493a-b128-f092d9a89042">
      <Text>(looking up)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="a63938c9-eca1-4276-a891-9771397ae4b8">
      <Text>No fucking way.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="0108b843-e69a-4309-9e51-7a2204f49758">
      <Text>SKYLER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="34fc5ed2-6a28-488b-a1df-44c6498dc3a9">
      <Text>Phoenix in the house, bro!</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="702e7861-f0ff-435a-a437-e2802ce775d8">
      <Text>TANNER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="a675a3fd-8654-442b-82f2-25ec38aa064c">
      <Text>(appreciatively)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="948aab32-1d79-4a20-9300-3a3a91315d35">
      <Text>Broseph. What are you wearing?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="a6837930-8809-4ca2-915a-0249c3e17dda">
      <Text>Jaz walks to the table. Every eye follows. The jacket still half-zipped, she looks like she just crawled out of a punk show gutter.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="29f663f2-200d-4368-9f43-cd87066faab0">
      <Text>She did.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="865a536f-a201-4c14-980c-d66102944953">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="52f29d3e-d1bc-4192-8438-c3dd1f770be1">
      <Text>Good to see you too, Tanner. Love the pocket square. Very... tangerine.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="9d5aa851-5267-4b8c-9168-07110ae52b4c">
      <Text>TANNER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="0643604b-5fb4-4d41-9c49-2c97cb983ca6">
      <Text>It's coral, actually—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="778db393-d09a-4ce7-808d-c4d00848f50f">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="21ec31ad-b96b-44f3-a687-c38788acee5f">
      <Text>I don't care.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="7f274f91-9e4f-46c0-ae0e-834dc143ae0d">
      <Text>She pulls the banded ten thousand from her jacket. Tosses it to the nearest muscle in the corner. He catches it without changing expression. Counts it. Nods to someone unseen.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="b503d4ac-7710-4553-ad9e-564fb658d9f9">
      <Text>A moment later, another man appears with a rack of chips. Sets them in front of her.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="f9d59707-a35d-4c7a-abbe-f72ff8266c6b">
      <Text>BRAD</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="231f76bc-f61f-40e4-bad4-2cdc97d93ec5">
      <Text>Dude, bro, seriously—the outfit. What is this, post-apocalyptic lingerie?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="ff3edaf6-9477-42e1-891a-ad9906e49712">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="cb0766af-4a3d-4ca1-8c52-b0b01c31c7ad">
      <Text>(sitting, stacking chips)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="880c58d0-171d-4b70-8a38-881f2481078d">
      <Text>You want to talk fashion or you want to play cards?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="f74dc665-ed4c-4352-a1b0-45e0491a9f01">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="12d3eb0b-1da6-409d-89cb-e7cc4e7a9011">
      <Text>Can we do both?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="c1d39682-36c1-4e02-a7c0-d1ff32ae38df">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="d7799a26-b6e7-4f06-8839-32dd7bd0b4ba">
      <Text>You can't do either, Hunter. That's why I keep taking your money.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="0d56536d-d7e1-4754-b2a6-2229f29b4670">
      <Text>JIMMY FONG</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="36bd2a83-88c9-4fc7-ae2e-3ad7d7f8e2ee">
      <Text>(cold)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="dea57605-9df5-49b5-9195-996716619e26">
      <Text>You cost me nine thousand dollars.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="077b5607-69e4-41b4-bab2-0805b66fc85e">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="b0f94b3f-17ce-4a1b-8253-a58b6c7c862a">
      <Text>(not looking up)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="0448b5fa-eb0c-4fe1-ad5a-01eca8d79266">
      <Text>I just collected it. You lost it.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="10d5c5b7-29cf-4434-846f-ff66cb6d9fe1">
      <Text>She finishes stacking her chips. Looks around the table. Smiles.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="ab720ff8-ea50-4175-a3db-90b36e6b10c6">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="22bba2e1-5a03-4b7e-94ac-c26384ff504a">
      <Text>So. Who's dealing?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Transition" id="bee74316-93b3-46d1-a693-d30558b2a86a">
      <Text>MONTAGE - THE GAME:</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="4a185c58-3556-4c68-bf69-39b1102fc938">
      <Text>— JAZ DOWN:</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="e28f794d-d83e-4528-9d59-5b3fcea01c59">
      <Text>The chip stack has shrunk. She's leaning forward now, studying faces. Jimmy Fong pushes all-in with a smile that shows too many old teeth. She folds. Watches him rake it in.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="5afab6d5-bc1c-483e-91c3-dd5a111bcfb1">
      <Text>JIMMY FONG</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="38cd8bf0-db04-4af9-b755-c55cc45770f6">
      <Text>Not so confident now.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="6f49f321-6f17-4744-946b-546a4658a4e3">
      <Text>A bottle of Johnnie Blue has materialized. Jaz is pouring herself a glass. Then another. Then another. Her play doesn't change. If anything, it sharpens.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d299b0a2-416b-41cb-9ac7-58e7b75e559a">
      <Text>— JAZ ALL-IN:</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="309185bc-542f-45f3-89b2-dbadc57ee9f9">
      <Text>She shoves her entire stack to the center. The table goes quiet. Chase is across from her, sweating through his Hermès tie.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="88619274-51da-4b84-857f-38428c2062f1">
      <Text>CHASE</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="0ca29709-0e52-4aa0-a907-1f2577d2cdb0">
      <Text>Bro. Dude. Broseph. I don't... I can't...</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="d3e55324-7db0-4ef9-b183-21e90f8cabf6">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="c38f7ca6-ee44-46d4-b362-43c142de937a">
      <Text>Call or fold, Chase. Some of us have places to be.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="f376e063-b006-4f51-820a-3bf01a369b53">
      <Text>He calls. She flips her cards. He flips his.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="5b19d649-32a3-4c43-b8bb-414a5d107e61">
      <Text>She wins.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="b0822fbc-df34-4637-b239-5100413e4ba7">
      <Text>CHASE</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="305a5a8c-7ae1-4245-8652-3e97607b0c25">
      <Text>FUCK!</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="3006b343-5c97-415b-b129-19a892bcb5e4">
      <Text>An ashtray overflows in front of her. She lights a fresh cigarette off the dying ember of the last one. The smoke halos her head.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="159ce05a-ad3a-40da-abeb-aca1b921cd88">
      <Text>— THE COKE VIALS:</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="677de7ea-5110-4039-8bee-64db2933a0b6">
      <Text>Later. Jaz's chips are gone. All of them. She's staring at a pot she desperately needs.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="1dd10690-ed5e-41d8-ad98-ae4cfa697488">
      <Text>She reaches into her jacket. Pulls out the vials from the green room. Sets it on the felt with a soft clink.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="ba392545-9bd7-43ba-8273-464099b0beac">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="79bad7c6-aa77-4aea-a031-c1897f9e79da">
      <Text>Peruvian. Uncut. Worth at least a grand.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="3bf2e9e0-6bd9-4607-98fc-aa4fe8c51fe4">
      <Text>The table considers.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="82c7058a-ea59-4d69-b103-d959a82958c0">
      <Text>SKYLER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="3e5652b5-dcc0-4f54-8a37-0c34247aed5d">
      <Text>(shrugging)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="437573d2-0987-4b12-9c8d-7cffc5ad498e">
      <Text>I'll allow it.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="cb4ada13-f48c-4d0a-9e95-e12e88f66144">
      <Text>She's back in.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="c5c5426f-1454-457d-b7d5-c3ae1a633e7c">
      <SceneProperties Length="6/8" Page="49" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. MCCORT TOWNHOUSE - MASTER SUITE - DAWN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="6c70e096-99a7-41da-8150-296982d0f19a">
      <Text>Gray light seeps through the automated shades. JANET stirs. Reaches out, instinctively, to the other side.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="359e4687-edd9-47d3-bbf8-2333b061eb80">
      <Text>Cold sheets. Kevin-shaped absence. She reaches for her phone on the nightstand. Unlocks it.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="6d4d97e7-a379-4419-af2a-9b484220f788">
      <Text>MESSAGES:</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="84dc513e-d40a-4124-8653-7d38c0d24d01">
      <Text>Nothing from Kevin. Not a text. Not a "good morning." Not a "big day, thinking of you." Nothing.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="e0dfae7e-d3aa-4a42-b9c4-5bbd1767e364">
      <Text>She scrolls.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="4b052e13-2e4e-4092-b786-ded98acd06bc">
      <Text>A message from MARCUS (TRAINER): [image]</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="2ae9dd73-be10-441a-8f46-018487a26e21">
      <Text>She doesn't react. Scrolls on.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="79f84c26-c6b9-4831-96a3-4dda9ae7f1e5">
      <Text>CHAD (HAMPTONS): [image]</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="4ae427de-47ee-49be-ad0e-c6bd2e37c941">
      <Text>Scroll.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="6c035637-57dd-44c2-963d-55fd8abc32f5">
      <Text>MICHAEL (HAMPTON POOL GUY): [image]</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="021390ef-1dbf-4bd6-965e-ecb49009aaff">
      <Text>UNNAMED (MET GALA AFTERPARTY): [image]</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="dd573c39-04a5-4de0-8f45-4ead86ccb9a7">
      <Text>Janet stares at the parade of phalluses. Different men. Different dicks. All before 7 AM.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="60ec53c2-4496-489f-86ce-6a641316582f">
      <Text>She sighs. Just... bored.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="6397f727-9a7f-4e18-a3b8-9a29ef0aa86f">
      <Text>She drops the phone on the bed. Stares at the ceiling. The phone buzzes again. She doesn't look.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="4a9d1ae3-8033-49ed-9934-9dec4ce0bd2f">
      <SceneProperties Length="3 7/8" Page="49" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="BRAD">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="HUNTER">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="JAZ">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="JIMMY CHO">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="SKYLER">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TANNER">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. BASEMENT POKER ROOM - CONTINUOUS</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="44a650c0-69fa-4b42-93bf-fe3bb08e4ca0">
      <Text>THE SUIT:</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="ac15a61b-9fe9-4b00-a5da-928ecdabb0cd">
      <Text>TANNER is no longer wearing his suit.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="a1fe4412-ceda-4caa-b685-4b893a53f1df">
      <Text>TANNER is wearing just his tangerine thong. Just the thong. Nothing else. He's still at the table, still playing, goosebumps visible in the basement chill.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="660cd6a7-c31a-43a6-9af2-57c9ed0acc1b">
      <Text>JAZ is wearing his dress shirt and suit jacket over her harness. The pants are draped over her chair—too big, unwearable, but claimed nonetheless.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="e84116d5-b439-4278-9b37-fa36e53f50cb">
      <Text>TANNER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="254d7439-0005-4041-8a8c-1af15eaa2455">
      <Text>(shivering)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="0fd2eb31-833b-4c89-8632-ea6b60ef5d87">
      <Text>This is humiliating.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="a171ec3f-0557-4c62-9a38-8451b7304593">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="dd34e509-b370-4258-bc58-89aba9825100">
      <Text>It's coral, actually.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="5f0d0337-19c3-4e97-b6b5-656bf57b4d30">
      <Text>She rakes in another pot.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Transition" id="9f5da4cd-b240-4852-a3be-f861c742e0ed">
      <Text>THE FINAL HAND:</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="e1f53a62-44a1-468b-8dff-00de022d3f5d">
      <Text>The Hunter pushes out cards. Jaz peeks—her face reveals nothing. Tanner peeks—and sits up straighter.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Transition" id="1f247463-9a89-4208-82b5-dc60abd7c1c4">
      <Text>THE FLOP:</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="7f9983e9-4fde-4de4-9770-44636ece897c">
      <Text>Jack of spades. Ten of spades. Nine of spades.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="f1d76323-abf3-44da-9927-310ae5b39754">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="14348d54-bb7f-4541-8199-21d0c6f16f9c">
      <Text>Spicy board, bro.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Transition" id="96912d1c-cd2e-465e-b2af-ab52414a877d">
      <Text>THE TURN:</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="33307545-563b-4f58-bf9e-c2d0d4fda30f">
      <Text>Six of diamonds.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="a3454e12-1865-4e06-8895-5e937bef2c9d">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="2c235fd6-376e-40ff-b695-463e1bb09ed2">
      <Text>(pushing chips)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="17c27f94-d3d0-426d-ab30-9629186088e9">
      <Text>I’m tired, gotta go, all in.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="13a816f9-c2f7-489e-bc7a-87dfff18f720">
      <Text>The table folds to Tanner as she gestures to her wall of chips. He looks at his cards. Looks at his nonexistent chips. His last went to the big blind. Looks at her massive stack, then at each of the other players, no one will make eye contact. JIMMY CHO across the table.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="7343e25d-4fcb-40ab-a2ce-4fea15c27e03">
      <Text>Tanner</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="39c36206-6ec7-469b-8de2-49997f818b96">
      <Text>(to the house)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="20378c7a-dc32-4ba6-93a0-1a3bdf95479c">
      <Text>Can I get a marker?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="b08bf84a-80dd-4b09-956e-e4b3949c66ac">
      <Text>The old man in the corner just shakes his head. No.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="639e0e9e-8f73-4f76-ad04-abdf71fb5124">
      <Text>TANNER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="71c5c4bc-12a1-48b0-9777-753e04f4a073">
      <Text>Jimmy. Bro.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="746afe96-868f-4fbc-9dc0-112a608c058d">
      <Text>JIMMY CHO</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="b7529319-fcd9-4e4e-a3d6-47ed46a736b8">
      <Text>Fuck off.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="3381f17e-d35c-4e79-bdcd-59be32c6ac69">
      <Text>TANNER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="36ec0c80-3cbf-4c86-a386-edd284f8a53b">
      <Text>I'm good for it. You know I'm good for it. Just let me use the Playboy thing as collateral—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="5b4cc0aa-7e35-4c9f-af29-a1835cb2a7d9">
      <Text>JIMMY CHO</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="f665e346-60e0-4b66-9c40-ea9e07c1f365">
      <Text>We just swiped that deal. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="5a03b4b3-d3cc-494f-a810-011cea738c61">
      <Text>TANNER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="a4b5b3fb-ffe8-4a78-8732-8b06925ff68a">
      <Text>Bro this is a sure thing. No sweat.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="1e565862-59bf-4379-9329-125107f82e13">
      <Text>Jimmy studies him. Studies Jaz. Studies the board.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="90b9388f-5379-4660-b8b1-b62c2160788f">
      <Text>JIMMY CHO</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="92ea4fda-d1d5-4e57-93a5-7f0991f9c072">
      <Text>(slow, dangerous)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="8bf7bcf9-641b-491b-8584-d32955e16ee5">
      <Text>Nothing is a sure thing.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="9b1f98bd-27e0-4b16-99f0-0c4bc034e702">
      <Text>TANNER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="5b7d28ac-fc2a-474a-a90f-f902505a8cb8">
      <Text>This is, bro. I swear.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="8729da55-b38c-4fd1-aa09-48daa68e0d05">
      <Text>A long beat. Jimmy reaches into his satchel. Pulls out a manila folder. Slides it across the table.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="167e3cb2-ea6f-466f-acf4-4d30168131ba">
      <Text>JIMMY CHO</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="d8812374-2cdb-4a7a-976f-e4658d082576">
      <Text>This is on you, either way, this goes bad, you will make it good. One way or another.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="bc984d88-48b3-46ea-a9fa-e07178bba32c">
      <Text>Tanner grabs the folder.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="949998d0-4c33-45d1-9fb5-31f6ae63685b">
      <Text>TANNER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="1be52fc2-51ef-4396-8d2a-80756aaf4875">
      <Text>No problem Bro! Trust me!</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="f8dbdbdb-8682-4a9c-bef6-f09fb2e526b2">
      <Text>(Slaps it down on the pot.)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="fe5d6541-bbeb-43bb-9a91-a23fcff0e811">
      <Text>Twelve mil in tax liens. Deed free and clear. Old Playboy resort in Jersey. Land's worth twenty easy.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="ece5f5d2-7682-4d4d-b7f2-13bbc46ab664">
      <Text>He looks at Jaz. Feels his cards. Confidence swelling.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="f10ac883-355d-4912-bf2d-2f86064ef991">
      <Text>TANNER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="9c47890a-3b52-4481-b8cc-1cbf7931422b">
      <Text>But no fucking way just to call. It’s too big.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="331a1f0a-346b-4f5f-8298-bb0a44e926f6">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="ae48dd0a-a466-44d2-b191-57960230c50b">
      <Text>Bro.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="17bdee6c-93c5-4f48-9b08-c198409fdb21">
      <Text>TANNER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="1d0e2c62-deb7-4a96-9766-350bff13c03a">
      <Text>(manic, greedy)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="b08a8c33-c03e-4f8c-bf36-8d37a4a7547c">
      <Text>what else you got to sweeten the pot. Or have you finally got nothing to say?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="5a973f83-c922-479d-9858-a24218051b8b">
      <Text>He stands— thong and all— cock sure that he’s finally got this little girl frightened at the big boy table after everything she’s taken from them.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="449b4ef4-5671-490c-8db5-07c1814ddd8e">
      <Text>TANNER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="6519e372-5641-4023-9d5c-cc61c63ace83">
      <Text>ALL IN. Plus what?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="b848987a-33df-439f-b336-2f66bd180a5c">
      <Text>The table erupts. Jaz doesn't move. She looks at the pot. Looks at her stack. Looks at the folder, pulls it, flips through the tax certificate, reads the deed.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="89af0e23-2147-4202-9248-1ecd8913591b">
      <Text>TANNER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="7514792b-1109-4fe2-9a72-6736ea620e32">
      <Text>(grinning)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="fa5c6a53-cf92-4c5e-b2db-18ea098f8052">
      <Text>What's wrong, Phoenix? after all these months you finally chicken.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="e7c5361b-aeff-4256-b74d-7d7690d030dd">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="e9dc6018-3d35-4658-8ad5-a1b97f5cc6e1">
      <Text>Pen. Paper.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="b5ff205e-7f35-4719-9c3c-edcaed8f7df3">
      <Text>Someone slides her a napkin and ballpoint. She writes. Slowly. Deliberately. The whole room sweating. She folds it. Slides it across the felt to Tanner.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="7110b2a6-71d2-45e3-9686-540b6b47a657">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="2bbcc069-a39c-41a1-bf33-f218d080b7c3">
      <Text>That covers my call.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="92300ec3-5583-46c2-bda7-2f69a0c80a60">
      <Text>Tanner takes it. Unfolds it. Reads. His expression shifts. His breathing changes. And— unmistakably— the tangerine thong twitches.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="2dc7b090-fc1f-4d2f-a62b-a0210408a4ad">
      <Text>BRAD</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="492906f8-7f87-45a7-b78a-e957cb7e5039">
      <Text>(watching Tanner's face)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="531f7c7f-ce49-4e1d-abef-017188a68db5">
      <Text>What? What does it say?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="52163512-0766-46fa-8c86-25bf14b7311c">
      <Text>Tanner doesn't answer. He's still staring at the napkin. Whatever's written there has him... affected.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="fb5e000b-3656-47d7-83ae-9a40241311a3">
      <Text>TANNER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="d564f82a-ad71-4b32-bb0f-7b3b261bbda4">
      <Text>(hoarse, not looking up)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="aed875bd-2aef-446d-a1e0-2181a0b5d8dc">
      <Text>Done.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="4a7e7493-f422-4229-ae2e-e5cf92e10b6b">
      <Text>He tosses the napkin into the pot. Doesn't hesitate. Doesn't negotiate.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="3bf6a680-ea92-452a-b788-8651395a5583">
      <Text>SKYLER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="6722d4fc-b474-409d-a01f-2d2b342f728b">
      <Text>Bro, what the fuck is on that napkin?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="c6101949-30c0-4535-939c-ef9c54077a84">
      <Text>TANNER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="fe93f208-522f-4aef-b42a-3d312a588700">
      <Text>(finally looking up, flushed, confident)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="e8134273-4898-4948-b292-803b2b6069c8">
      <Text>Doesn't matter. I already won.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="70657577-8d21-4427-82bd-c1295158899b">
      <Text>He flips his cards with triumph. Eight of spades. Seven of spades.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="eb551a3d-9025-4fcf-b46c-c570e0696064">
      <Text>TANNER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="9a2b4f7c-4377-48ea-a490-513b89b35570">
      <Text>Straight flush! Seven through jack!</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="51385611-7d94-40a8-a1a6-18dc2395202f">
      <Text>The table explodes. Tanner's already reaching for the pot—for the chips, for his suit, for the deed, for that napkin—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="5a686f05-ed59-4aa8-957e-386e93aa52ea">
      <Text>Then:</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="47ca936a-ebdc-4cc0-a3a4-9cb2b322a8b6">
      <Text>Silence. Jaz hasn't flinched. She reaches down. Flips the Queen of spades. The room goes cold. Flips the matched King.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="e74bf580-ad3e-4e2a-8e96-2a1934606910">
      <Text>DEAD SILENCE.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="f41403bd-f079-475f-9760-321a320148a5">
      <Text>Nine. Ten. Jack. Queen. King. All spades.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="c06941c6-5523-49a1-b0d4-792adaddb2fb">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="084b84fd-5ce4-494d-9d65-f00e8a3b9029">
      <Text>(whispered)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="fe45e343-6fa0-45bd-927d-eb498a78238e">
      <Text>Jesus Christ.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="1cad9695-9259-4da5-83ac-492002f0f403">
      <Text>Jaz stands. Sweeps the pot into her bag— chips, cash, the manila folder with the liens and deed. And the napkin. She plucks it from the pile. Folds it. Tucks it back into her jacket.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="45e1e057-c44b-43ab-8256-e1be884042a1">
      <Text>TANNER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="20e23e02-9225-4bf2-af83-721b70195c6e">
      <Text>(frozen)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="f0a75b8a-829b-4aca-b440-14ee641a9d03">
      <Text>No.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="c1277a66-5970-4537-872d-1b593e6a63e9">
      <Text>She turns for the door. Tanner lunges— The CORNER MEN drop him face-first into concrete before he takes two steps.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="807eeacf-5caa-4237-835f-2523fd1c0682">
      <Text>TANNER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="e6354196-cd23-499f-b766-0de4790ecf4d">
      <Text>(screaming, pinned)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="07d4093d-e48b-482e-b3dc-8e5ca8e7689d">
      <Text>JIMMY! JIMMY, I'M SORRY—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="ba80602f-892c-47c4-b517-ac6017187838">
      <Text>Jaz reaches the door. Looks back.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="85971822-37fb-4cc8-a62b-76bee8877a25">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="45c9d82e-8ef4-4931-8fe5-b62214ac3685">
      <Text>Thanks for the game, boys.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="3cbfde68-0c24-421c-a0c3-612d6061b114">
      <Text>She walks out.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="7d5e65e1-398e-478f-ab26-994a79ad700b">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="53" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. STAIRCASE - CONTINUOUS</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="4691c456-187f-4f27-a47d-9cd4ba14622b">
      <Text>Behind her, muffled chaos—screaming, crashing, violence. She climbs the stairs past the hanging duck carcasses, through the dark kitchen, to the front door.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="076ccf58-afa7-45d1-89bf-7791b73b1b6f">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="53" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>EXT. CHINATOWN - DAWN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="ab1fe76c-e391-407b-b27e-abb24e1bdba8">
      <Text>Gray morning light. The city waking up. Jaz stands on the sidewalk. Bag heavy on her shoulder. Quarter million in cash. Twelve million in tax liens. The deed to a place she's never seen. She pulls out her phone. Texts Jamie: "Won a hotel." Three dots. Then:</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="505aa173-9292-4a8a-aaf7-462a1c671439">
      <Text>JAMIE: "???"</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="6499be3e-8543-4be2-96c6-91b98809b9d2">
      <Text>She smiles. Starts walking toward the subway.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="8c2baef3-c1d4-4cd3-9a9e-1eebcbd24736">
      <SceneProperties Length="1" Page="54" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="KEVIN">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. TOWN CAR - dAWN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="723bbf73-12be-4805-99b9-83842182b7dc">
      <Text>KEVIN in the back seat. Fresh suit. Coffee thermos. Phone pressed to his ear. The morning sun cuts through Midtown glass, making everything golden. He looks like a man who owns the world.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="3297f710-4098-4419-8361-1f4aef7af815">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="f0fb737b-c87a-490f-9fdb-52b82e8ecc66">
      <Text>Dude, I'm like a block away from my desk.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="2bc6e575-d576-48d5-b67a-a658c0a448d1">
      <Text>Beat. Listening.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="3870f431-5703-4b02-9930-84165d723fbb">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="a90d9974-408d-4a4d-9a46-1f89ea911aa7">
      <Text>Yeah, I signed it myself last night. Before I left. Didn't want any delays on the authorization.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="c3821834-9b60-461c-9849-e1e9e1e6c68e">
      <Text>Beat.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="9fca52fb-f156-464a-83d0-b524436aea84">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="f46de8c2-170e-4859-a5c5-adbeea4160d8">
      <Text>The filings should be registered in Munich already. They're like five hours ahead of us.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="6a75fcd8-5978-48c0-97ae-cbcd69e9bfa5">
      <Text>The car slows. Kevin glances out the window, annoyed. Through the glass: FLASHING LIGHTS. NYPD cruisers. Unmarked sedans. A lot of them. All clustered in front of a building. His building.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="9207261f-6e29-44c2-b3ae-94111f576bb4">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="43066a6f-716e-45e3-b30d-67806b2da85b">
      <Text>(dismissive)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="770c8c75-b8e5-420b-b763-d261b171cf58">
      <Text>Fuck. There's some cop bullshit in front of my building.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="713e7a37-d9d3-4f79-b6fb-c6d108e2ea1f">
      <Text>He cranes his neck, trying to see past the obstruction.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="ebc19cfa-60d5-44c1-9535-e7dd8919ed5e">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="80af249c-3bcc-4c7b-bae1-a8d1a2909be6">
      <Text>Probably some anti-ICE dickheads picking a fight with cops again.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="2fca261a-2c74-40ad-acd0-ddc8f5eb31eb">
      <Text>Beat. Listening.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="ffb9f990-8abd-4e16-b385-fc6574324492">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="584c1715-0b77-4c2d-af68-f239bec624e1">
      <Text>Yeah. Call you in ten.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="45b56485-23e0-4a8e-98fd-56d18d09e036">
      <Text>He ends the call. Scrolls for news.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="b12cd6fc-7f3d-4202-b7a7-11c9e44b6146">
      <SceneProperties Length="5/8" Page="55" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="JANET">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. MCCORT TOWNHOUSE - KITCHEN - dAWN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="61ae1e16-fb6d-43c9-9fbe-6a341106cecf">
      <Text>JANET at the counter. Lululemon. Hair in a perfect messy bun. Glowing skin. The picture of wellness.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="1a1ab60d-dfcf-45ff-9aef-efdc5f9b7ee1">
      <Text>In front of her: two artisanal bowls of Greek yogurt topped with fresh berries, granola, a drizzle of honey. Instagram ready.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="c9cb532f-7212-4474-99ef-06a3ccc0a001">
      <Text>She checks her phone. 6:43 AM.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="c5f0369d-c05a-4c1f-9a3d-b743e8d0117e">
      <Text>JANET</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="1da688a1-22b5-420e-bc6c-0b9f4aa9375e">
      <Text>(calling upstairs)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="6e0490ca-e1d1-402e-a498-03b2e1627e1e">
      <Text>Jamie! Jazzy! You're going to be late!</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="7742b8cd-f8d4-466d-8107-40d856bb4a22">
      <Text>No response.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="ac3e84ac-5653-449e-95b5-ea99645ea306">
      <Text>JANET</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="3035fdac-bf25-4673-b948-761735c14881">
      <Text>I made breakfast!</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d0b7f3f6-8dde-4fe5-a43e-55b4bf9a2856">
      <Text>Still nothing.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="43e56bb9-2ebd-4ef0-a95c-c40ba9ed07ed">
      <Text>She sighs. Picks up her coffee. Takes a—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="1b34bd42-2805-4b9b-a1ff-7c5c124b88c0">
      <Text>BOOM. BOOM. BOOM.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="3f0a9737-823f-48f6-aff3-00023d38490e">
      <Text>The front door. Not a knock. A pounding. The kind that rattles the frame.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="c4a98f97-3b91-4d05-8e18-52ddd3d3a6e1">
      <Text>The coffee cup slips. Shatters on the marble.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="a7bdbba0-1048-43b9-ac4a-c86ed5dde475">
      <SceneProperties Length="4/8" Page="55" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. JAMIE'S BEDROOM - SAME TIME</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="4d8216c5-5436-48a1-843f-24d0ca1cfb73">
      <Text>JAMIE at his monitors. He heard the pounding.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="8de9396c-9f84-4e44-b845-ce33d3ca978d">
      <Text>He moves to the window. Peers through the blinds.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="24f7fc11-6d74-46a6-a92b-7353ad012663">
      <Text>On the street below: Police cruisers. Three of them. Unmarked SUVs with Government plates. And in the windshield of the nearest one—a portable emergency light, flashing red and blue.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="5f6e4a86-b1b1-4378-a0a8-9ad6700881e0">
      <Text>BOOM. BOOM. BOOM.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="32ae021f-6f49-4754-94ce-6786a055888f">
      <Text>His face goes white. He doesn't panic. He executes.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="e4a5eb7a-a265-4129-b090-d1758130486d">
      <Text>From under his desk: a power drill. Already charged. Waiting for this moment.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="7c7f59a5-c764-424a-a5fd-07ff18c69dff">
      <Text>From the tower: three hard drives. Quick-release bays. They slide out in seconds.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="ba54119f-35a7-449e-a913-7b55465b3d05">
      <Text>He sets the first one on the floor. The drill screams to life.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="ce064dc2-2aa7-478c-a15b-7d90290b2ab6">
      <Text>He drives the bit straight through the platter. Metal shrieks. Sparks fly. Data dies.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="c65685d9-6001-4506-b8fa-4892251d229e">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 1/8" Page="56" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="KEVIN">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="NYPD DETECTIVE #1">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="NYPD DETECTIVE #2">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>EXT. KEVIN'S OFFICE BUILDING - MORNING</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="eeb7f4b2-7462-41ea-bb95-b6dde95e7b99">
      <Text>The town car door opens.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="6b9728ae-ebf4-450b-91a0-a2f5bae0a8cb">
      <Text>KEVIN steps out, coffee in hand, phone in the other, already composing his first email of the day—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="19d6a4f6-3358-4c93-832f-72b0bbb46ca1">
      <Text>Two police detectives materialize from nowhere.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="08181f36-c975-4339-8e79-b6dfb95fa751">
      <Text>NYPD Detective #1</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="07776518-90e1-4add-8837-8663438bbc9e">
      <Text>Kevin McCort?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="025b0cb0-52d7-4553-9751-1bbc3259f65a">
      <Text>He barely looks before they grab him.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="2ab1356b-b40a-4e8b-b327-458e8e464b25">
      <Text>The coffee explodes on the pavement. The phone clatters into the gutter. His face SLAMS onto the hood of his own town car— </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="4194ebd5-6a92-41e7-8837-edb77cb8bb2e">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="9c94fb68-c901-4f76-a105-209185728d73">
      <Text>WHAT THE FUCK—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="cecb92b3-cf45-4f63-9067-c09e9b57d84c">
      <Text>His arms are wrenched behind his back. Cuffs bite into his wrists. The Patek scrapes against metal.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="55e85348-32c7-41ac-aa4a-12554a32c679">
      <Text>NYPD Detective #1</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="b41598ca-8173-4aab-a1c1-3ea964e9ebcd">
      <Text>Kevin McCort, you're under arrest for securities fraud, wire fraud, and money laundering.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="d714f27d-6eb8-4d4a-8eaa-46e178b51376">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="a4dcf208-ae51-4181-bee0-b86a17b75cb6">
      <Text>THIS IS A MISTAKE—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="70fd47ad-c33b-4506-b6ae-1b343d65ca36">
      <Text>NYPD Detective #2</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="daa8ff84-cc46-41df-b03b-807eb3012a37">
      <Text>You have the right to remain silent.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="79867be3-fc8e-4eb3-b946-8449affabd56">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="e23ee248-adcf-426e-b80d-be1a28c4fb73">
      <Text>I'M THE COO— CALL CHET MASTERS— HE'LL EXPLAIN—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="012f4c27-9e45-43a8-b50a-d04a22a8a883">
      <Text>NYPD Detective #2</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="16c8ef28-16b2-4aea-b7b6-7d33dfbbca07">
      <Text>Anything you say can and will be used against you in a court of law.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="52a10a54-3288-4d96-9a8e-bc417d0285d7">
      <Text>They haul him off the hood. His face is red with pressure and rage and the first creeping edge of terror.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d55bd6be-4529-49c0-8a4e-63fa39a5da9d">
      <Text>The agents drag him toward a waiting sedan.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="dd6f9b3b-0eec-48ac-97ca-fbcd032b3ad2">
      <Text>NYPD Detective #2 </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="f825e504-859e-4108-b743-b60c798ea2b9">
      <Text>—if you cannot afford an attorney, one will be provided for you.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="4dae847f-32f9-40dc-abe5-0539eaa8fddc">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="f01364f5-c0a9-4012-ac7a-02b7400cb374">
      <Text>(into the back seat)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="db87f193-6cbb-4899-8e03-a0eec9725ca1">
      <Text>I CAN AFFORD A THOUSAND ATTORNEYS, YOU FUCKING—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="1db1b7ce-53be-4624-a9dc-89cde808b139">
      <Text>The door slams shut.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="d2aeaea8-f945-41fe-93ec-39a7c7e83350">
      <SceneProperties Length="6/8" Page="57" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>EXT. 79TH STREET SUBWAY STATION - late dawn</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="64517aba-576f-4eac-b109-af272d2c9408">
      <Text>The 1 train rumbles away beneath the grate. JAZ emerges from the stairs into the morning light. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="1945284b-082e-4bf9-ab91-a38164097c4c">
      <Text>She looks like a beautiful car wreck— Tanner's suit jacket over the harness, his dress shirt half-buttoned, combat boots, the shaved half of her skull catching sun. Smudged eyeliner. Cigarette dangling from her lips. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="01f9af80-15b4-4bab-ab9d-4d6eba13bbf7">
      <Text>The messenger bag hangs heavy on her shoulder, her leather tucked into the strap. She's exhausted. Triumphant. Done. She pulls out her phone. Checks the lock screen.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="5a7bf87e-db85-4c6d-b848-cba0e910f23a">
      <Text>JULY 14TH, 2026.    6:52 AM</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="72b3af23-15af-4a14-bfbb-155d8aa1d6df">
      <Text>She stares at the date. Reaches into her jacket. Pulls out the napkin. Unfolds it. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="721f37aa-6f2a-491b-98e9-f5ef2151eabd">
      <Text>Jaz looks at it. The thing she was willing to bet. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="51f5ded9-9f9e-409b-b7e6-fbc7b80b4f98">
      <Text>She takes a long drag of her cigarette. The cherry glows bright. She touches it to the corner of the napkin. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="07d4d8c6-ce92-4add-9c70-449eb4d85642">
      <Text>The paper catches. Flame crawls across it, blackening, becoming smoke. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="778b7daf-6533-4b1a-99d3-b412799d8a16">
      <Text>She holds it between two fingers, watching it burn, playing with the flame as it eats toward her hand. At the last moment, she lets go. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="aea3e32d-ba02-4a74-ac10-fedff7f093d9">
      <Text>The ash scatters on the sidewalk. Gone. She exhales smoke. Starts walking home.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="1887f0cd-c747-45c3-883f-7e06c115e832">
      <SceneProperties Length="2 7/8" Page="57" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="DA INVESTIGATOR">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="JAZ">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="NYPD DETECTIVE">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>EXT. WEST 84TH STREET - CONTINUOUS</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="79e7dada-077f-476c-b492-1f198bc5d531">
      <Text>She's half a block away when she sees it. Light. Flashing. Reflecting off the limestone facades of her neighbors' townhouses. Red and blue strobing against brownstone and brick.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="25f0d008-3a7e-4c7c-ba40-3517224c2d15">
      <Text>She slows. Unmarked sedans. Four of them. Parked at angles in front of her building. City plates. Two NYPD patrol cars blocking the street at either end, uniformed officers holding the perimeter. And a white van — no markings she recognizes yet — idling at the curb.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="4cae9028-84b3-4483-887b-95fe35e5e269">
      <Text>JAZ </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="9934857e-db55-413b-b5e3-f9ca10a27c84">
      <Text>(under her breath)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="3b99a644-e641-4b79-987f-11075890f33c">
      <Text>No.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="1dcced1b-09b6-49e1-a25e-265a2c5df0d5">
      <Text>She speeds up. Starts running. The messenger bag bounces against her hip. Combat boots pound pavement. The suit jacket flaps open, the harness fully visible, the punk underneath completely exposed.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="11009cfa-fa2c-40c6-9b43-41e3c1d80556">
      <Text>She rounds the first sedan—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="f8c70562-a323-45e8-b8cb-d2ffedf0da02">
      <Text>And sees her mother.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="5077037e-7ec1-4cc9-8f7f-11d55b33ef7e">
      <Text>JANET is in handcuffs. Still in her Lululemon. Hair still in that perfect messy bun. Two plainclothes DA INVESTIGATORS are guiding her into the back of an unmarked car, one hand on her head, pushing her down.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="3cee9ab2-1787-47fc-baf3-d30ecadf9ca2">
      <Text>Janet's face is blank. Shell-shocked. The mask finally, completely gone — and nothing underneath but terror.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="f2903781-6d63-4248-bcab-4d4ff6dac4ce">
      <Text>JAZ </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="913b7e2e-2dbc-4bdd-b8bc-ff3e52fe76b4">
      <Text>MOM!</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="946b4899-15be-4270-834d-f2677ea1798c">
      <Text>Janet's head snaps toward the sound.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="26a8c7f6-17f9-43b3-88bf-9523f4e3745d">
      <Text>Their eyes meet.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="6efbe28b-9647-4463-8083-412290b79b26">
      <Text>For one moment, mother and daughter see each other — really see each other. Janet in cuffs, Jaz in punk skin. Both exposed. Both stripped of their disguises.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="7f952e7e-7c2f-4f14-b18f-abfaaad39b63">
      <Text>Then the investigators push Janet into the vehicle. The door slams shut.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="91811357-6aa4-4902-8518-8f01f9d86157">
      <Text>And across the sidewalk — a different kind of horror.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="c324ed39-17ff-4e76-be92-522f82a104de">
      <Text>JAMIE. In his hoodie, barefoot — they pulled him from his room mid-drill, he didn't have time for shoes. He's standing on the sidewalk between a UNIFORMED OFFICER and a woman in civilian clothes — an ACS CASEWORKER with a lanyard and a clipboard, talking at him like he's a problem to be filed.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="7ea4c895-64b3-48c8-9ed6-2f5ba61212ff">
      <Text>The caseworker puts a hand on Jamie's shoulder. Guides him toward the white van with the city logo on the door — ACS. Administration for Children's Services.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="8d6c2f97-fc96-4e17-bb4e-a1a2073ba637">
      <Text>JAZ </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="79855cc6-0753-43c2-8bba-851c2d4bbd76">
      <Text>JAMIE!</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="6e36c00f-0594-4863-91da-ead62099e750">
      <Text>She lunges for the sedan holding her mother. Pounds on the window with both fists.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="48cb9547-7e59-4e05-88e2-33b694683e8d">
      <Text>JAZ </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="736572e1-c73d-4a4d-86a5-88d7d2feb399">
      <Text>MOM! MOM!</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="62cba395-2ef5-4322-9ed2-8ee2226d4121">
      <Text>The engine revs. The vehicle starts to move. A hand grabs her shoulder. DA INVESTIGATOR, trying to pull her back.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="50e9122a-e7eb-48c1-a3da-7762a7dc5545">
      <Text>DA INVESTIGATOR </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="3b4f9889-3b79-494d-83c4-cbfbf2a07926">
      <Text>Ma'am, you need to step away from the—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="b3586850-cc1b-4393-8821-0c6854e89e42">
      <Text>Jaz spins. Her fist connects with his nose. Clean. Fast. The sound of cartilage cracking. The investigator staggers back, blood already streaming through his fingers.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="d287ed41-717d-46df-9fdf-016743c37cc3">
      <Text>DA INVESTIGATOR </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="22aa9f15-aefb-46fc-8665-8788e056bfa9">
      <Text>FUCK!</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="54f0c7e8-d40f-4ebc-bbb2-3ca4b124ed92">
      <Text>Other officers react — hands going to holsters, bodies tensing —</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="ed1dc32f-9f9d-44ba-aa7b-ada8f541abea">
      <Text>NYPD DETECTIVE </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="7e365c4a-826b-4297-b5e4-b7fb40e33635">
      <Text>(hands up, palms out) )</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="f68880dc-1154-4166-8136-b20c54b941a7">
      <Text>Easy. EASY. Everyone calm down.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="96b412e8-6d2f-4813-a66d-f138b8879383">
      <Text>Jaz steps back. Breathing hard. Fists still clenched. Blood on her knuckles that isn't hers.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="75c857be-6237-41be-9d40-0624994cd566">
      <Text>The sedan with her mother pulls away. Turns the corner. Gone. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="2d854bd2-dc7c-482c-b1ba-05c808dc577a">
      <Text>The ACS van with Jamie is rolling now too — and through the rear window she sees him. Her little brother. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="6c264f5e-845b-49f9-9556-d3060f10d364">
      <Text>He puts his hand on the glass.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="ff0ef9ee-c4bd-42f7-8108-7a34b10f348c">
      <Text>The van turns the corner.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="f477f5c7-6202-4e2d-ac0b-b849741d42e4">
      <Text>NYPD DETECTIVE </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="ff8943cd-70fd-433d-af23-9877fa8243f9">
      <Text>(slow, careful)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="cc705e1d-f6b0-46c0-b986-37c07f07a523">
      <Text>Miss. Miss. We need you to stay calm. Can you do that?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="4a019df1-c949-4baa-ab32-8c2a47ab5c14">
      <Text>Jaz doesn't answer. She's looking past him. At the townhouse.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="58e1def7-18b2-4353-bc36-547e6021d379">
      <Text>Yellow tape. Everywhere. Crisscrossing the door, the windows, the garden gate. Bold black letters repeating on an endless loop:</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="62febc2d-ed44-4399-aa4a-fe4796deed84">
      <Text>CRIME SCENE — DO NOT CROSS</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="21ec507b-2383-4bfc-bfc8-360a17fc3234">
      <Text>The lilies in the foyer window — she can see them through the glass. Still in their vase. Still disheveled. Evidence now.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="dac014f8-6bdf-459b-86f4-1b945f0991f8">
      <Text>NYPD DETECTIVE </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="06936bb6-c4c8-4a37-934d-eb5eb2575dfc">
      <Text>Are you Jazmine McCort?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d6d7c4f7-0612-4f1a-a1fa-de593fa6b5ca">
      <Text>She turns to look at him. This detective. This man in his NYPD jacket with his hand still extended like he's calming a wild animal.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="f94519ce-2857-487b-8757-a973bb8140f1">
      <Text>And behind him: her neighbors. Peering from windows. Standing on stoops. Watching. Filming.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="e4e53619-2489-4e4d-8e17-9adfc455adeb">
      <Text>Watching Jazmine McCort — perfect Princeton-bound daughter of Kevin and Janet McCort — standing in the street in a leather harness and combat boots, half her skull shaved and tattooed, blood on her hands, her parents in state custody, her brother taken by children's services, her home sealed, her entire life a lie that just stopped working.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="22becd1e-84ff-44c5-aa6c-e6fddea19125">
      <Text>NYPD DETECTIVE </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="99485e5f-9ee1-496a-a73d-b30b02dfeb0f">
      <Text>Miss McCort? Do you have somewhere you can go?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="e11367c9-2d0e-4324-bd0c-297d85510757">
      <Text>Jaz stands there.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="2735ed93-d306-4109-830c-1678fcc6b15e">
      <Text>The bag on her shoulder holds everything she has left. Cash. Chips. A deed to a building she's never seen in a town she's never been to.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="dc8eff9f-ec4a-480a-a04e-9fff0a53aff1">
      <Text>She has nowhere to go. She has no one to call. She is completely, utterly alone.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="b3b4cb13-ec09-474c-9760-0da0555bda8d">
      <Text>It's going to be a beautiful day.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Transition" id="638cd063-243d-40ca-9799-fb3f8f076a7c">
      <Text>SMASH TO BLACK.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
  </Content>

